<HEADLINE> City Police in Asian Cup Winners Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- South China of Hong Kong,
China, secured a semi-final berth in East Asia when they beat
visiting Ho Chi Minh city police of Vietnam 3-0 here on Thursday
in the second leg of the second round of the 10th Asian Cup
Winners Cup 1999/2000.
</P>
<P>
In the first leg, South China drew city police at 1-1.
</P>
<P>
South China, who was runners-up in 1994 in the event, dominated
the match with better teamwork and skills. They found the net
twice in the first half and sealed the victory with another goal
in the second half.
</P>
<P>
South China will take on Bangkok Bank of Thailand in the semi-
finals of East Asia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
