<HEADLINE> New Age Group Project Introduced at FIG Extraordinary Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 14 (Xinhua) -- A new age group project was
introduced at the International Gymnastics Federation (FIG)
extraordinary congress which ended here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new age project, which plans to train young gymnasts in
five-step program from the very beginning to the world elite level,
aims to protect those teenagers from injury.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia, Cameroon and the Lesotho were admitted as FIG new
members while five federations, including Sudan, Central African
Republic, Virgin Islands, Bosnia-Herzegovina and Turkmenistan,
were expelled from the FIG for their long-time default of annual
membership fees.
</P>
<P>
Three sports, namely sports aerobics, trampoline and sports
acrobatics were adopted as new disciplines of FIG.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from 69 countries and regions participated in the one-
and-a-half-day FIG extraordinary congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
