<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Mourns Death of Nyerere </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
secretary-general of the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
Thursday sent his condolences to Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa on the death of former Tanzanian president Julius Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his condolences to and sympathy for the Tanzanian
government on behalf of the OAU, Salim spoke highly of Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
The late Tanzanian leader dedicated his life to the cause of
freedom, independence and unity, as well as the socio-economic
development of Africa, Salim said.
</P>
<P>
"His tireless crusade for liberation, and the leadership he
gave to the struggle as president of Tanzanian and Chairman of the
Frontline States, was substantial in the defeat of colonialism and
apartheid," the OAU chief noted.
</P>
<P>
The death of Nyerere, one of the founding fathers of the OAU
and one of Africa's wise men, "is an irreparable loss and a void
that will be difficult to fill," Salim said.
</P>
<P>
"Africa has lost an ardent advocate of its unity and
indefatigable defender of the freedom and dignity of its people,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere died of leukemia in a London hospital on Thursday
morning at the age of 77. 
</P>
</TEXT>
