<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Disappointed at U.S. Vote on CTBT </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU) Said
Thursday that it is disappointed at learning that the U.S. Senate
has decided in a vote on Wednesday to reject the ratification of
the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT).
</P>
<P>
"We have underlined our firm conviction that the treaty is
strongly in the interest of all states as an essential barrier to
the proliferation of nuclear weapons. This continues to be our
conviction," the EU said in a presidency declaration.
</P>
<P>
"We continue to be committed to working for its entry into
force at the earliest opportunity," said current EU president
Finland on behalf of the 15 EU member states.
</P>
<P>
The EU also urges all states which have yet to ratify to do so
without delay, "in particular those states, including the United
States, whose ratification is necessary to bring the treaty into
force". 
</P>
</TEXT>
