<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cape Verde Launches Campaign Against Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Cape Verde Thursday launched the
National Program of Combatting Poverty, Angola's official news
agency Angop reported.
</P>
<P>
As part of Cape Verde's national development plan, the
ambitious anti- poverty program is aimed at a sustained and
durable reduction of poverty from which 30 percent of the
country's population have been suffering.
</P>
<P>
According to the program, women who are responsible for
subsistence in Cape Verde's families, manual-labor workers,
unemployed and young people are targets of the program.
</P>
<P>
With 50 percent of the initial finances guaranteed by the World
Bank, the four-year program can be prolonged because the whole
campaign against poverty is very complicated.
</P>
<P>
The program provides the country's projects up to 30,000 Cape
Verde contos (300,000 U.S. dollars), will averagely consume 1.5
million contos (15 million dollars) every year.
</P>
<P>
Cape Verde, a west African archipelago state and one of the
poorest countries in the world, is in scarcity of mineral
resources for future industrial development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
