<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Through As Opponent Walks Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia cruised into the quarter-finals of the Austrian Trophy
indoor tennis tournament after his Dutch opponent pulled out with
a knee injury on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
But fourth seed Tim Henman, who lost in the final of Basle just
a few days before, was upset 6-4, 2-6, 6-3 by Russian Marat Safin
in the first round.
</P>
<P>
The Briton, who was still seeking his first win after one-year
title draught, had not come out of apparent disappointment from
his consecutive loss.
</P>
<P>
Fifth seed Greg Rusedski of Britain, winner of the Grand Slam
Cup, beat Andrei Medvedev of Ukraine 4-6, 7-5, 6-3 in the second
round.
</P>
<P>
Playing in the seventh week in a row, Rusedski said he was both
mentally and physically tired after the win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
