<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Jazz's Stars Malone, Hornacek Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Karl Malone and Jeff
Hornacek are unable to play in the Utah Jazz's exhibition opener
Wednesday night against the Vancouver Grizzlies because of injury.
</P>
<P>
Malone, the Most Valuable Player last season, injured his back
last week during training. Hornacek injured his right leg in
practice earlier in the week.
</P>
<P>
The Jazz also scratched forward Pete Chilcutt, who is suffering
a sore lower back.
</P>
<P>
The Grizzlies will play without forward Antonie Carr, who had a
sore right knee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
