<HEADLINE> Chamberlain Died of Heart Trouble </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Wilt Chamberlain died of
heart failure, the great basketballer's agent Sy Goldberg said
Wednesday in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
"He had congestive heart failure," Goldberg said the day after
Chamberlain died at age 63. "He had deteriorated relatively
quickly over the last month or so."
</P>
<P>
Michele Hamilton, associate clinical professor of cardiology at
UCLA, said: "Most likely, with a man of his age group dying
suddenly, it would be from blockage in the blood vessels, causing
an irregular heartbeat, regardless of his past medical history."
</P>
<P>
Funeral services for Chamberlain are scheduled for Saturday.
Chamberlain's sister, Barbara Lewis, said her brother had
undergone dental surgery last week and looked worse than she had
ever seen him.
</P>
<P>
The greatest basketball player ever in the world scored a
record 100 points in a game against the New York Knicks on March 2,
1962. He also snatched a record of 55 rebounds against the Boston
Celtics on November 24, 1960.
</P>
<P>
He scored 31,419 points and grabbed a record 23,924 rebounds.
</P>
</TEXT>
