The president accepted an invitation for the match in order to
encourage Uganda soccer fraternity. He is a sportsman and wants
to prove that, Thursday's New Vision daily reported quoting FUFA
Secretary Godfrey Kisekka.
</P>
<P>
The invitation follows a challenge from the president that
local sports officials organize a match in which he would play
instead of being invited to the stadium as a spectator, the
newspaper reported. 
