<HEADLINE> Chevron's Daily Oil Output in Angola to Hit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chevron, a leading petroleum
company in the world, announced here Thursday that its daily oil
production in Angola is expected to increase by 100,000 barrels
from November.
</P>
<P>
Kenneth Derr, president of the U.S.-headquartered company,
revealed the actual production capacity of Chevron is 460,000
barrels per day, twice higher against 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The president said that the growth of the production will be
realized with the start of exploration in November in Block 14,
one piece of the offshore oil fields.
</P>
<P>
Derr noted that his company has another project in Block 14, a
piece of offshore oil field near Angola's central-west Province of
Benguela, which will help the company promote the oil production
in Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
