<HEADLINE> Russia Tightens Security at Nuclear Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Atomic Energy and
Interior Ministries have taken additional measures to tighten the
security at nuclear power plants and other nuclear facilities, the
Interfax news agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The move was made at recommendations from the Federal Security
Service (FSB), the main successor to the Soviet KGB, following
reported threats from Chechen rebels that they would sabotage such
facilities.
</P>
<P>
FSB spokesman Alexander Zdanovich said his service has set up a
special department to ensure the safety of nuclear facilities,
Interfax reported. 
