<HEADLINE> Patriotic Song Warmly Greeted in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The song entitled "Five Star
National Flag" presented during the evening gala celebrating the
50th anniversary of the founding of New China was warmly received
by the Chinese and caused a great stir nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The patriotic song, composed specially for the 50th anniversary,
has been turned into a MTV program featuring a variety of flag-
raising scenes, by the Beijing Television Station.
</P>
<P>
Although the song has a political theme, it has gained great
popularity among the Chinese because of its beautiful melody,
inspiring lyrics, and the patriotism the five star national flag
stands for in the hearts of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
The five star national flag represents the past tribulations of
the Chinese people, their pleasure in victory, and their great
expectations for the future, according to the song's composer,
Tian Ming.
</P>
<P>
"I hope the song will bring everyone together, by inspiring
patriotism and idea of national cohesion," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yongfeng, a renowned Chinese mountain climber, said he
felt his heart quake when he heard the song. "The song is so
inspiring to me because the five star national flag is a sacred
symbol to every alpinist," he said. "During the final sprint
toward the summit, a climber may abandon camera, food, clothing,
and even oxygen, but the flag is something indispensable and we
must plant it on the summit we have conquered." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
