<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong police and customs
seized over 796,000 pornographic items including 698,000 VCDs
during the 1999 campaign against pornographic materials which
ended on September 30.
</P>
<P>
Some 361 persons that were suspected of breaching the
provisions of the Control of Obscene and Indecent Articles
Ordinance were arrested in the 328 operations, according to a
briefing Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The campaign was jointly launched in mid-July 1999 by the
Police, the Customs and Excise Department, and the Television and
Entertainment Licensing Authority (TELA).
</P>
<P>
Esmond Lee, assistant commissioner for Television and
Entertainment Licensing, said that the three enforcement
departments stepped up action against retail black spots and
suspected wholesale outlets and manufacturing plant, thereby
minimizing young people's access to pornographic materials.
</P>
<P>
"TELA also enhanced young people's understanding of the bad
influence of pornographic materials through publicity and public
education," he said. 
