<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Military Garrison Opens PLA Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 14 (Xinhua) - The Hong Kong Garrison of the
People's Liberation Army (PLA) Thursday opened a military museum
depicting the history of the PLA garrison in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), attended the inauguration ceremony
for the Hall of Military History of the PLA forces along with PLA
officers from the Guangzhou military area command.
</P>
<P>
Covering an area of more than 1,100 square meters and
comprising five parts with over 800 photographs and objects, the
museum features the history of the PLA garrison since its
formation on the mainland, its arrival in Hong Kong following Hong
Kong's return to the motherland in mid-1997 and the background of
its ground, naval and air forces.
</P>
<P>
The museum is located at the site of the Prince of Wales which
was the former British army headquarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
