<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China-WHO Committee Meets in Qingdao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The 21st Meeting of the China/
World Health Organization (WHO) Joint Coordination Committee (JCC)
opened Wednesday in this coastal city in east China's Shandong
Province.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, the last one in this century, will audit the
implementation of the 1998-1999 program and discuss new
cooperation projects in the next few years.
</P>
<P>
There will be an introduction to the making of China's public
health plan for the 2001-2005 period and to the four major areas
of cooperation between the WHO and China. Namely, the prevention
and treatment of tuberculosis, the reform of public health
services, the control of tobacco, and the health of the aged.
</P>
<P>
The JCC, an annual high-level meeting between China and the WHO,
was initiated in Beijing in 1979, and is held in the Philippines
and China alternatively. This is the 11th time the meeting has
been held in China.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the Chinese Ministry of Public Health, the
WHO, the United Nations Development Program and several other
organizations are attending the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
