<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canadian Prime Minister Expresses Condolences over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien expressed condolences Thursday over the death of former
Tanzanian president Jiulius Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, Chretien said Nyerere "led and
nurtured the emergence of Tanzania as an independent state" in
years of struggle for change throughout the African continent.
</P>
<P>
He also praised the former Tanzanian leader for his "unmatched"
contribution to "the struggle against apartheid".
</P>
<P>
Nyerere, 77, died of chronic lymphocytic leukemia in a London
hospital Thursday morning. The founding president of the country
led Tanganyika to independence from Britain in 1961 and
masterminded its union with Zanzibar in 1964 to form Tanzania.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
