<HEADLINE> CSRC to Support Development of GEM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The China Securities Regulatory
Commission (CSRC) signed exchange of notes today with the Hong
Kong Securities and Futures Commission on listing inland Chinese
enterprises on the Growth Enterprise Market (GEM) in the Stock
Exchange of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Zhengqing, chairman of CSRC, said today that CSRC will
support the expansion of GEM, and will further improve cooperation
with its Hong Kong counterpart to ensure the healthy development
of both GEM and inland Chinese enterprises to be listed.
</P>
<P>
The Stock Exchange of Hong Kong launched the Growth Enterprise
Market in October 1998 to offer a venue of business expansion for
small and medium-sized companies.
</P>
<P>
So far, GEM has accepted dozens of applications from
enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
