<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More User Friendly Measures at HK Airport Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Airport Authority (AA)
announced Thursday a number of measures to make Hong Kong
International Airport more user friendly.
</P>
<P>
The measures include the provision of trolleys in the airside
area, the introduction of duty free shopping for arrival
passengers, the offer of half-hour free parking, and the launch of
a discount for passengers who park their car at the airport.
</P>
<P>
The measures are welcomed by airlines operating in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
AA Chief Executive Officer Billy Lam Chung-lun said that the
measures for passenger convenience complement the announcement in
September by AA Chairman Victor Fung of initiatives for air cargo
and airport charges reduction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
