<HEADLINE> Tonga King Leaves Shanghai for Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 14 (Xinhua)-- Taufa'ahau Tupou IV, the King
of Tonga, left Shanghai this morning for Xiamen, a major port city
in east China's Fujian Province, to continue his state visit to
China.
</P>
<P>
During his four-day stay here, the king met with Shanghai Mayor
Xu Kuangdi and visited some local factories.
</P>
<P>
The king arrived in Beijing last Wednesday at the invitation of
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
The king paid an informal visit to China in 1997. Diplomatic
ties were forged between the two nations on November 2, 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
