<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Electric Vehicle Symposium Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Vice Premier Wu Bangguo
addressed the opening of the 16th International Electric Vehicle
Symposium (EVS-16) here today and said the Chinese government will
continue to increase its support of research and development for
electric vehicles and related technologies.
</P>
<P>
Electric vehicles, Wu noted, will play a significant role in
enhancing energy efficiency and improving the global environment.
</P>
<P>
The EVS-16, co-sponsored by the Electric Vehicle Association of
Asia Pacific, the Society of Automotive Engineering of China, and
the China Electrotechnical Society, is being attended by some 480
officials, experts and entrepreneurs from 35 countries and regions,
with treatises coming from the world's top automotive companies
including General Motors, Ford, Toyota, Renault, and Nissan.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the symposium, an international electric car
exhibition was launched here Tuesday, and General Motors, Ford,
Toyota, and Renault have sent their concept vehicles to the show.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
