<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: China's Exports to Top Ten Partners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Following are the latest facts
and figures about China's exports to the top ten trade partners in
the first three quarters of this year, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to the United States reached 30.04 billion U.S.
dollars, up 10.7 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Hong Kong reached 26.01 billion U.S. dollars,
down 13.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Japan hit 22.46 billion U.S. dollars, up 6.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to the European Union (EU) increased 5.2 percent to
21.29 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN)
reached 8.52 billion U.S. dollars, up 9.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to the Republic of Korea was 5.34 billion U.S.
dollars, up 19.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Taiwan was 2.79 billion U.S. dollars, up 1.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Australia was 1.90 billion U.S. dollars, up 13.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Canada was 1.72 billion U.S. dollars, up 12.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Russia was 880 million U.S. dollars, down 37.1
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
