<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FM Spokeswoman Refutes EU's Criticism of China's Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking at a regular press conference, Zhang pointed out that
the Chinese government has been carrying on continuous efforts to
protect and improve the human rights and basic freedom of all
Chinese ethnic groups, and tremendous progress in this area has
won global recognition.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government resolutely opposes attempts by any
country or any group of countries to interfere in its internal
affairs with the excuse of human rights and by distorting the
truth, according to the spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
Due to different national conditions among countries, it is
normal that they hold different views on the issue of human rights,
she said.
</P>
<P>
"China is ready to continue dialogues and exchanges with the EU
on human rights on the basis of equality and mutual respect in
order to enhance mutual understanding and properly solve
differences," the spokeswoman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
