<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Romanian Friendship Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji in a
meeting here today with Romanian Foreign Minister Andrei Plesu
said that China values Sino-Romanian ties and regards the Romania
as China's good friend and partner in central and eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
He said that no matter what happened in the world and within
the two countries, the bilateral friendship has not been affected
since the diplomatic relations were forged 50 years ago.
</P>
<P>
China would like to further its cooperation with Romania in
various fields, he added.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also expressed his appreciation for Romania's adherence to
the one China policy.
</P>
<P>
Plesu said that the development of the bilateral relations is
satisfactory and there are no political conflicts between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian government firmly supports China's position on the
issues of Taiwan and Tibet, he said, adding that the top priority
at present is to cement the economic cooperation and two-way trade.
</P>
<P>
Romania welcomes the investment of Chinese companies, he said.
</P>
<P>
Plesu also conveyed Romanian Prime Minister Radu Vasile's
regards and invited Zhu to visit, for which Zhu expressed his
thanks.
</P>
<P>
Plesu is here at the invitation of his Chinese counterpart Tang
Jiaxuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
