Bilateral cooperation in political, economic and cultural
fields have been fruitful since the two countries resumed their
diplomatic ties, said Zhang, adding his belief that the current
visit will further increase bilateral friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Zhang also briefed the guests on China's principled stand
toward the Taiwan issue, saying he is grateful for Guinea Bissau's
adherence to the "One-China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Mane said that China was the first country to provide aid to
Guinea Bissau during its struggle against colonialism, and the
people of Guinea Bissau shall never forget this. The Guinea Bissau
government and people hope to continue the relationship with China
and shall always stand by China, he added. 
</P>
