<HEADLINE> Chinese, Romanian FMs Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan held talks with his Romanian counterpart Andrei Plesu here
today.
</P>
<P>
Noting that this year marks the 50th anniversary of the
founding of the diplomatic relations between China and Romania,
Tang said, no matter what occurred in the international arena, the
two countries has maintained their friendship, respected each
other and treated each other as equals.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are "friends indeed in time of need," Tang
said.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that China respected the independence, sovereignty
and territorial integrity of Romania, respected the development
path chosen by the Romanian people, and was ready to work together
with Romania to further promote the bilateral relations of
friendly cooperation in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Plesu said he was delighted to visit China on the occasion of
the 50th anniversary of the two countries' diplomatic relations,
saying that the two countries maintain good bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Also, the two countries carried out effective cooperation on
the international stage, such as in the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the current visit to be a new starting point for the
growth of bilateral ties in all fields, in particular in trade and
economic cooperation. Romania welcomes Chinese investment, he told
Tang.
</P>
