<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets Participants at ASEM Science Ministers Meeting (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The premier said the Chinese government attaches importance to
science and technology development and cooperation and exchanges
with other countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that to date, China has established scientific
cooperation ties with 152 countries and regions and has become a
member of over 800 international academic organizations.
</P>
<P>
He explained that since the start of this year, China has
quickened the pace of restructuring and reforming scientific
research institutes and adopted a series of major measures for
scientific development-related investment and trade and
intellectual property rights.
</P>
<P>
Zhu emphasized that politicians, businesspeople and scientists
from various Asian and European countries have reached consensus
that it is most important that they promote scientific and
technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said the convening of the current meeting will further tap
the potential for cooperation among Asian and European countries
and expand the areas of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and Minister of Science and
Technology Zhu Lilan also attended the meeting.  
</P>
