<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets Participants at ASEM Science Ministers Meeting (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
stressed here today that so long as the Asian and European
countries adhere to the principle of equality and mutual benefit,
they can smoothly usher in a new era of scientific cooperation in
the next century.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier also emphasized the importance of
respecting intellectual property rights and focusing on long-term
interests in scientific cooperation while meeting here this
afternoon with participants at the ongoing first Science and
Technology Ministers Meeting of the Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM).
</P>
<P>
Zhu gave a warm welcome to the participants at the two-day
meeting which opened this morning.
</P>
<P>
He said the convening of the meeting turns a new page for
scientific and technological cooperation among Asian and European
countries, and is a major event for the development of friendly
cooperation between the two continents.
</P>
<P>
The premier said Asia and Europe are both important sources of
human civilization and that the continents began spreading and
exchanging scientific discoveries via the ancient "Silk Road" many
centuries, bringing well-being to the people of the two continents
and contributing to world civilization.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said scientific exchanges and economic and trade
cooperation have become an important part of international
relations.
</P>
</TEXT>
