<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier: Asia-Europe Scientific Cooperation Has Great Potential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Scientific cooperation among
Asian and European countries has great potential, Chinese Vice-
Premier Li Lanqing said at a banquet here this evening for the
first Science and Technology Ministers Meeting of the Asia-Europe
Meeting (ASEM).
</P>
<P>
Li said the meeting, which opened this morning, is the first
high-level meeting concerning regional scientific cooperation
between Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
This meeting indicates that the scientific and technological
cooperation among Asian and European countries will enter a new
stage, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He said statesmen, businesspeople and scientists from various
Asian and European countries have come to realize that further
coordination and promotion of scientific cooperation and
technological exchanges between the two continents will benefit
the scientific development of each and stimulate the regional
economic and social growth.
</P>
<P>
He said that the strengthening of cooperation will also promote
peace, stability and prosperity of other countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier said that China attaches importance to the
scientific and technological cooperation with Asian and European
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese Government has signed scientific
cooperation agreements with the governments of Japan, the Republic
of Korea, some members of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) and a number of European Union (EU) countries.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China signed with the EU a science and technology
agreement last December.
</P>
<P>
He said the scientific and technological cooperation between
Asian and European countries is mutually complementary, adding
that Asia has the manpower and is rich in resources of agriculture,
forestry and biological engineering.
</P>
<P>
Li said the European countries have vast experience in
scientific research, education, development of manpower resources
and industrialization of scientific discoveries.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the setting up of a scientific cooperation
mechanism by the ASEM members will benefit Asian and European
countries alike.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Minister of Science and Technology Zhu Lilan, ministers
in charge of science and technology affairs from 25 ASEM members,
and representatives of the Commission of the European Union
attended the banquet.  
</P>
</TEXT>
