<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Mourns Death of Tanzanian Ex-President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe Thursday sent a message of condolence to the government and
people of Tanzania over the death of its founding president Julius
Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
In the message to Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa, Mugabe
said that Tanzania and the rest of the world had lost a great man.
</P>
<P>
The history of Zimbabwe and southern Africa would be incomplete
without a chapter on Nyerere's "the revolutionary, visionary,
principled, indomitable and unyielding supporter of our own and
the region's independence," said Mugabe.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe would remain indebted to Nyerere and the people of
Tanzania for their contribution to its independence, he added.
</P>
<P>
"That candle can never be extinguished and will remain his
eternal legacy," Mugabe said.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere died of leukemia at the age of 77 in a London hospital
on Thursday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
