<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Deplores U.S. Rejection of Test Ban Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Foreign Minister Lloyd
Axworthy expressed regret Thursday at the rejection of the United
States Senate to ratify the Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban Treaty
(CTBT).
</P>
<P>
The world "can only be deeply disturbed by this turn of
events," Axworthy said, adding "Canada, the United States and the
rest of the world will be much more secure with the CTBT than
without it."
</P>
<P>
He also urged the U.S. Senate to reconsider its decision on the
CTBT in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The treaty fell 19 votes short of the required 67 for
ratification, with 48 senators in favour, 51 against and one
abstention. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
