<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Mourns for Tanzanian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni Thursday sent a message of condolence to the government
and people of Tanzania on the death of former Tanzanian president
Julius Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
In the message to Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa, Museveni
referred to Nyerere as a statesman who had made a most outstanding
contribution not only to the people of Tanzania, but also to the
people of Africa as a whole.
</P>
<P>
"By supporting the anti-colonial movement in southern Africa
and by supporting the people of Uganda against the dictatorship of
Idi Amin during his tenure of office, Nyerere made a most
outstanding contribution to the liberation of approximately 100
million people," Museveni said in a press release issued here by
the President's Office.
</P>
<P>
He assured Mkapa that the people of Uganda will never forget
the fact that almost single-handedly, Nyerere shouldered the
burden of fighting the black dictator Idi Amin.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere was hailed as almost the only president in Africa who
ignored the erroneous argument of the pseudo-sovereignty of states
that was used to cover up the genocide unleashed by Idi Amin on
the people of Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The present economic and political recovery of Uganda would not
have been possible without that invaluable contribution of the
former Tanzanian leader.
</P>
<P>
To show Ugandan people's heartfelt sorrow and sadness, Museveni
 announced that all the national flags in the country would be
flown at half- mast until Nyerere's remains have been buried at a
date to be announced by the Tanzanian government.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere, who had been suffering from leukemia, passed away at
the age of 77 at a London hospital on Thursday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
