<HEADLINE> British PM Mourns Death of Tanzanian Ex-President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 14 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister
Tony Blair has expressed condolences on the passing away of
Tanzania's founding president Julius Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
In a message of condolence to the government of Tanzania, Blair
praised the role Nyerere played in making peace both at home and
abroad.
</P>
<P>
"He (Nyerere) was a leading African statesman of his time and
the founder of modern Tanzania," the British leader said. "The
fact that Tanzania is today a country at peace with itself and its
neighbors is in large part a tribute to 'Mwalimu' Nyerere."
</P>
<P>
British Minister of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs,
Peter Hain, said upon arrival in Dar es Salaam on Thursday morning
that Nyerere was a " grandfather to modern Africa, loved and
respected by the whole continent and the international community."
</P>
<P>
Nyerere died of leukemia at the age of 77 in the St. Thomas'
Hospital in London on Thursday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
