<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Mourns Death of Tanzanian Ex-president </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian President Negaso
Gidada Thursday sent message of condolences to his Tanzanian
counterpart Benjamin Mkapa over the passing away of former
Tanzanian president Julius Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian Foreign Ministry said that Negaso expressed his
deep grief on behalf of the people and government of Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian president said in his message that Africa has
lost a great leader and a great human being.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere did not belong to Tanzanians alone. "As a true, wise
and proud Pan-Africanist, he belonged to us all," said Negaso.
</P>
<P>
The struggle he waged, both for political emancipation and
later for economic liberation was on behalf of Africa and of all
those who were denied justice, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Tanzania's loss is therefore our loss, and its grief our
grief," he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prime Minister Meles Zenawi also sent message of
condolences to Tanzanian President Mkapa over the death of
Nyerere, the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere, who was treated for leukemia in a London hospital,
died on Thursday morning at the age of 77. 
</P>
