<HEADLINE> Mubarak Condoles on Death of Former Tanzanian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
on Thursday offered his condolences over the death of former
Tanzanian President Julius Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
In a cable of condolence sent to Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa, Mubarak described Nyerere as the "symbol of independence."
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of Nyerere's contribution to the independence
of Tanzania and forging African unity.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere, 77, died on Thursday of leukemia in London, where he
had been under treatment since September.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere led the campaign for the independence of his East
African nation from British rule and became the country's first
president in 1961.
</P>
<P>
Known throughout Africa as Mwalimu, or "teacher" in Swahili,
Nyerere retired from the presidency in 1985. He was among the few
African presidents to voluntarily leave office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
