<HEADLINE> Canadian Car-makers Pioneer Cleaner Fuel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- In a bid to further reduce
vehicle emissions, the big three U.S. automakers in Canada are
pioneering cleaner fuels in part of the country.
</P>
<P>
Ford Canada Ltd., GM Canada and DaimlerChrysler Canada Inc.
Thursday launched the joint program by announcing their
designation of pumps selling cleaner-burning fuels with an "Auto
Makers' Choice" logo.
</P>
<P>
The automakers said "cleaner cars need cleaner fuels to operate
properly and obtain maximum emissions reductions," even though
emissions from cars and trucks made by the big three have "reduced
by up to 99 percent from uncontrolled levels."
</P>
<P>
The automakers will forge a partnership with Atlantic Canada's
largest gasoline retailer Irving Oil to provide cleaner fuels on
the east coast, Quebec and Ontario.
</P>
<P>
The new fuels contain lower sulphur content and fewer fuel
additives, which are harmful to the pollution control equipment
fixed in the vehicles made by the three companies, the automakers
say.
</P>
<P>
"If all vehicles on the road in Canada today could access Auto
Makers' Choice gasoline, it would be the equivalent of eliminating
the smog-causing emissions from almost two million cars and light
trucks," according to Maureen Kempston Darkes, president of GM
Canada.
</P>
<P>
The automakers also asked other oil companies to follow suit in
making cleaner fuels for consumers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
