<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J.
Habibie Thursday night said his cabinet had taken concrete steps
to address the crisis and restore gradually and consistently the
life of nation and state.
</P>
<P>
In his three-hour accountability speech before the plenary
session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) here, Habibie
said his administration and all layers of the nation have exerted
its utmost to solve the country's accumulated and complex
problems.
</P>
<P>
