<HEADLINE> Mozambique Opens Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 14 (Xinhua) - Mozambique's long awaited stock
exchange market opened in Maputo on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Planning and Finance Minister
Tomaz Salomao declared that the success of the market will depend
on businesses and ordinary citizens understanding the advantages
they can obtain from it.
</P>
<P>
He said that the launching of a capital market in Maputo is a
sign of the confidence that investors on the Mozambican economy.
</P>
<P>
He recognized that the capital market is currently small, but
believed " we shall grow just as the capital markets in other
southern African countries have grown."
</P>
<P>
The stock exchange started with the trading of treasury bonds
of 60 billion (4.6 million US dollars) issued last May.
</P>
<P>
The first company to be quoted on the stock market will be
Cervejas de Mocambique (CDM -Beers of Mozambique), the privatized
brewing company, in which the majority sharehoder is South African
Breweries. CDM made net profits of 11.3 million US dollars in
1998.
</P>
<P>
At a later stage, the government intends to use the Stock
Exchange to sell off the shares it still holds in some 1,000
companies that have been privatized.  
</P>
</TEXT>
