<HEADLINE> Brazilian President Hails Sending of Brazil-China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZILIA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernanado
Henrique Cardoso congratulated Thursday the successful launch of a
Brazil's satellite built in cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
President Cardoso made the statement after having received this
report form Brazil's Minister of Science and Technology Ronaldo
Sardenberg from China.
</P>
<P>
The President conveyed his satisfaction to Minister Sardenberg
for the success of the satellite's launching and wished for the
success of the Brazil- China joint space program.
</P>
<P>
The operation took place at Taiyuan Launching Center, Shansi
province, at 1:06 (Brasilia time), on October 14, said Sardenberg.
</P>
<P>
This satellite has an objective to collect information about
the Earth's environment, agriculture, city planning, water
quality, besides the application of activities as environmental
monitor.
</P>
<P>
The governments of Brazil and China signed on July 6, 1988, an
accord to build and launch two satellites and CBERS-2 will be put
together and integrated next year.
</P>
<P>
This program has a total cost of 300 million dollars, of which
100 million are Brazil's responsibility and the other 200 million
dollars from China.
</P>
<P>
Sardenberg highlighted that Brazil and China have good
cooperation in the space program, adding that Brazil totally
trusts China's personnel and technology. 
</P>
