<HEADLINE> FAO Says Number of Hungry Still High in Poor Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Almost 800 million
people in developing countries go to bed hungry every night,
according to the U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO)
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
That is more than the combined population of Europe and North
America, said FAO, adding that some 200 million children in the
developing world are severely stunted.
</P>
<P>
Despite a 40 million decline in 37 countries in the 1990s, the
number of the chronically undernourished in the rest of the
developing world has actually increased by almost 60 million, FAO
said in its latest report.
</P>
<P>
It unveiled for the first time the picture of hunger in the
developed world where an estimated 8 million is undernourished.
</P>
</TEXT>
