<HEADLINE> EU Summit Attracts Over 1,200 Journalists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAMPERE, Finland, October 14 (Xinhua) -- A special summit of the
European Union (EU) to be held here over the weekend has attracted
some 1,200 journalists.
</P>
<P>
Most of them, nearly 900, are correspondents and reporters from 30
European countries who are much more interested in covering the event
on EU affairs.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting includes two working sessions, one focusing on
the establishment of a European Area of Justice and the fight against
crime, the other centering on a comprehensive migration and asylum
policy.
</P>
<P>
There will be some 35 television networks covering the meeting,
and they have booked over 200 saatellite time slots, current EU
president Finland said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The presidency said Reuters, the BBC and the EU Commission are
using their own satellite equipment. In addition, 44 news agencies and
51 radio stations are covering the summit. 
