<HEADLINE> Each Mozambican Woman Bears 6 Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MAPUTO, October 14 (Xinhua) - The average Mozambican women
bears 5.9 children in her life, according to statistics from the
1997 census released in Maputo this week.
</P>
<P>
This figure is already 13 percent lower than that in 1980
which stood at 6.8.
</P>
<P>
 Some 29 percent girls aged between 15 and 19 have become
mothers in the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
 One of the reasons for the high fecundity is that most
Mozambicans both men and women want large families.
</P>
<P>
The census showed that the gross birth rate is 44.4 per 1,000,
while the gross death rate is 21.2 per 1,000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
