<HEADLINE> Chile Insists on Pinochet's Freedom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chile's government Thursday
formally requested Britain to leave life-long senator Augusto
Pinochet free, due to humanitarian and heath reasons.
</P>
<P>
The note was delivered Thursday in London to the Foreign Office
and then was sent to British Home Secretary Jack Straw so that he
may read it.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday British judge Ronald Bartle ruled that Pinoched be
extradited to Spain to face another trial requested by Spanish
Magistrate Baltazar Garzon, who is accusing him of crimes and
tortures of Chileans and foreigners, among these dozens of
Spaniards.
</P>
<P>
The senator's lawyers will appeal in coming days against judge
Bartle's decision, and afterward the case will pass on to the
London High Court in December. 
</P>
