<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Africa Mourns Death of Tanzanian Founder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- African leaders have sent their
 condolences on Thursday to the late founding father of Tanzania
Julius Nyerere, saying Africa has lost a great leader and a great
man.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere, former president of Tanzania from 1964 to 1985, died
of blood cancer leukemia in a London hospital on Thursday morning
at the age of 77.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere did not belong to Tanzanians alone, "As a true, wise
and proud Pan-Africanist, he belonged to us all," said Ethiopian
President Negaso Gidada.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe said that the history of
Zimbabwe and southern Africa would be incomplete without a chapter
on Nyerere's " revolutionary, visionary, principled, indomitable
and unyielding support of our own and the region's independence".
</P>
<P>
"That candle can never be extinguished and will remain his
eternal legacy," Mugabe said.
</P>
<P>
Secretary-General of the Organization of African Unity (OAU)
Salim Ahmed Salim spoke highly of Nyerere, one of the founders of
the OAU.
</P>
<P>
"His tireless crusade for liberation, and the leadership he
gave to the struggle as president of Tanzania and Chairman of the
Frontline States, was substantial in the defeat of colonialism and
apartheid,"
</P>
<P>
"Africa has lost an ardent advocate of its unity and
indefatigable defender of the freedom and dignity of its people,"
Salim said.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni said, "By supporting the
anti-colonial movement in southern Africa and by supporting the
people of Uganda against the dictatorship of Idi Amin during his
tenure of office, Nyerere made a most outstanding contribution to
the liberation of approximately 100 million people."
</P>
<P>
Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi said Tanzania, east Africa and
the entire continent had lost a selfless son and a statesman who
dedicated his life to the cause of African dignity.
</P>
<P>
South African President Thabo Mbeki said Nyerere was a pillar
of strength to oppressed people all over the world and served as a
source of great inspiration to efforts towards Africa's rebirth.
</P>
<P>
"He was one of the wise sons of Africa who guided our journey
towards placing Africa in her rightful place in the world."
</P>
<P>
Mbeki said the best way to pay tribute to Nyerere was for the
African people to re-commit themselves to the cause of peace,
stability and a better life for all.
</P>
<P>
Some African countries will fly their national flags at half
mast to mourn for the death of Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin sent a message of condolences to
his Tanzanian counterpart Benjamin Mkapa, praising Nyerere for his
contribution to the friendlh at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
"He was a leading African statesman of his time and the
founder of Modern Tanzania," Blair said. "The fact that Tanzania
is today a country at peace with itself and its neighbors is in
large part a tribute to 'Mwalimu' (teacher) Nyerere." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
