<HEADLINE> More Refugees Expected to Return to East Timor: U.N. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) said it signed an agreement with
Indonesia Thursday on the free access to refugees across West
Timor where some 230,000 East Timorese are camped.
</P>
<P>
The agreement followed similar verbal assurances given to High
Commissioner Sadako Ogata by Indonesian President B.J. Habibie
during Ogata's visit to Jakarta last month.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR said it has flown over 1,500 East Timorese from West
Timor since last Friday. On Wednesday, the airlift capacity
doubled with the international Organization for Migration (IOM)
joining the airlift effort by using two more aircraft.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR hopes to return up to 2,000 people daily with the
imminent opening of a land corridor between West and East Timor.
</P>
