<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, October 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- The International Labor Organization (ILO)
Wednesday called on African nations to declare the AIDS crisis a
continental disaster and take actions to curb the killer disease.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made in an AIDS action program for Africa
announced in a statement at the end of three-day conference by the
United Nations agency in Windhoek, Namibia. (Africa-AIDS)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Former British Defense Minister George Robertson
formally took his new post Thursday as NATO secretary-general to
succeed Spain's Javier Solana who stepped down last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Robertson, whose appointment was decided on early August, will
host the Fifth NATO-Japan Security Conference Friday at the NATO
headquarters in Brussels to discuss the security situation in
Europe and the Asia-Pacific region, NATO said in a statement. (
NATO-New Chief)
</P>
