<HEADLINE> Greenpeace Criticizes U.S. Senate's Rejection of CTBT </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Greenpeace organization in
Greece Thursday criticized the U.S. Senate's vote opposing the
ratification of the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) on
nuclear weapons, saying the decision has "torpedoed" international
efforts to ban nuclear testing.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here Thursday, Greenpeace said the U.S.
Senate has begun a new cycle of "nuclear terrorism" and given the
green light to other countries with nuclear capability to ignore
the world's desire for a definitive end to the "nuclear nightmare.
"
</P>
<P>
Greenpeace Campaign Director Nikos Haralambidis said the U.S.
refusal to ratify entails the collapse of the treaty, which has to
date been signed by 154 countries. 
</P>
