<HEADLINE> State of Emergency Enforced in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 15 (Xinhua) -- State of Emergency has been
enforced throughout Pakistan with immediate effect, announced a
proclamation of emergency issued here in the wee hours of Friday.
</P>
<P>
Army Chief General Pervaiz Musharraf has assumed the office of
the chief executive of Pakistan, two days after the army took over
power through deposing former prime minister Nawaz Sharif in a
bloodless coup.
</P>
<P>
The Constitution has been suspended and the national and
provincial assemblies have been dissolved, but the president of
Pakistan shall continue in office, according to the proclamation.
</P>
<P>
The whole of Pakistan shall come under the control of the armed
forces of Pakistan, the proclamation added.
</P>
<P>
The order also announced the dismissal of the prime minister,
the federal ministers, the ministers of state, advisors to the
prime minister, parliamentary secretaries, the provincial
governors, the provincial chief ministers, the provincial
ministers and advisors to the provincial chief ministers.
</P>
<P>
This proclamation shall come into force at once and be deemed
to have taken effect on and from October 12, 1999, it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
