<HEADLINE> Abacha's Son Charged with Murder in Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The son of Nigeria's late
military ruler Sani Abacha Thursday was charged with murdering
late President- elect Moshood Abiola's wife at a court in Lagos,
Nigeria's largest city.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed Abacha, 29, was charged alongside General Sani
Abacha's security chief, Major Hamza al-Mustapha, and three other
security officials.
</P>
<P>
The court in its first session refused to accept an application
from the defendants for bail and decided to adjourn the case until
mid- November.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of people watched junior Abacha and his father's
colleagues walking into the courtroom with seemingly calm and
relaxation.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Abiola was shot dead in a Lagos street in June 1996, three
years after his husband won a general election and claimed himself
 the president.
</P>
<P>
General Abacha seized power and jailed Moshood Abiola after
the election was annulled by the military. Abiola died in prison
from a heart attack, a month after General Abacha himself died.
</P>
<P>
Major al-Mustapha and another accused, Lieutenant-Colonel
Ibrahim Yakassai, also face murder charges over the death in
prison in 1997 of Major-General Shehu Musa Yar'Adua, who was
deputy to current President Olusegun Obasanjo when he was a
military ruler from 1976 to 1979. Both Yar' Adua and Obasanjo were
jailed by Abacha in 1995 for allegedly plotting against his
regime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
