<HEADLINE> Chissano Pays Homage to Nyerere </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano on Thursday evening said in a radio address that the late
former Tanzanian president Julius Nyerere was a friend of his
country in difficult times.
</P>
<P>
Chissano described Nyerere as his country's first friend and
Tanzania led by Nyerere as "the cradle of freedom and
independence" of his country.
</P>
<P>
In 1962, Nyerere sponsored the founding of the Mozambique
Liberation Front (FRELIMO) in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
Chissano said Nyerere had been "always at our side, in our
difficult moments, and in our moments of celebration".
</P>
<P>
"Nyerere was present in the support for our struggle against
the destabilization and aggression we suffered from the racist and
minority regimes of Rhodesia and South Africa, and their allies
and agents," Chissano said in his condolence message.
</P>
<P>
Chissano praised Nyerere's role as the first chairman of the
Front Line states, "whose decisive role led to the total
liberation of the peoples of southern Africa from colonial and
racist rule".
</P>
<P>
In recent years Nyerere had continued his work "for peace and
freedom in Africa, and was leading the current process for
pacification in Burundi".
</P>
<P>
 The best way to pay homage to Nyerere, he concluded, was "to
restate our firm commitment to cooperation between the Mozambican
and Tanzanian peoples and states".
</P>
<P>
Nyerere died of leukemia in a London hospital Thursday
morning. He is to lie in state in London's Westminster Abbey on
Saturday before his body is flown back to Tanzania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
