<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, October 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia said Thursday that its ties with NATO remain
frozen and Moscow is not taking part in any joint activities with
NATO aside from the peacekeeping operations in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"The readiness of NATO to better take into account Russia's
interests and concerns regarding fundamental European and
international security issues may become a prerequisite for the
unfreezing of relations between Russia and NATO," Russian Foreign
Ministry spokesman Vladimir Rakhmanin said. (Russia-NATO-Ties)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia on Thursday voiced serious concern over the
refusal by the U.S. Senate to ratify the comprehensive nuclear
test ban treaty, saying it marked a worrisome trend in U.S.
activities recently.
</P>
<P>
Moscow is "disillusioned and seriously concerned" about the
Senate's decision, which "deals a serious blow to the whole system
of agreements in the field of nuclear disarmament and non-
proliferation, especially as far as the non-proliferation treaty
is concerned," Foreign Ministry spokesman Vladimir Rakhmanin said.
(Russia-US-CTBT)
</P>
