Fischer and Anna Lindh, said here today that they were deeply
disappointed at a U.S. Senate decision to reject the ratification
of the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT), a global pact
targeted at ending nuclear tests worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Senate decision represents a serious setback for
nuclear non-proliferation and disarmament and is therefore a wrong
signal, said the foreign ministers in a joint statement, adding
that they "deeply regret" the rejection.  (Germany-Sweden-US-CTBT)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- The Greenpeace organization in Greece Thursday
criticized the U.S. Senate's vote opposing the ratification of the
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) on nuclear weapons, saying
the decision has "torpedoed" international efforts to ban nuclear
testing.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here Thursday, Greenpeace said the U.S.
Senate has begun a new cycle of "nuclear terrorism" and given the
green light to other countries with nuclear capability to ignore
the world's desire for a definitive end to the "nuclear nightmare.
" (Greece-US-CTBT)
</P>
