<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Tractors Sell Well in Off-Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China's tractors have sold
surprisingly well this July and August, the traditional off-season
for buying the vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the China Tractor Statistics Society indicate
that in July and August, the country produced more than 8,800
large and medium tractors, up 22 percent over the same period last
year, with the sale number soaring 27.8 percent to 9,770.
</P>
<P>
Insiders in the sector attribute the growth mainly to the fact
that tractors with 50 horsepower and above have been well received
in the market, and that the boom season has arrived earlier in
markets of Jiangsu, Hebei, Shandong and Shaanxi provinces.
</P>
<P>
China's tractor production has maintained a steady growth
momentum this year. From January to August, 43,972 large and
medium tractors were manufactured, up 11.1 percent, and those with
over 50 horsepower jumped 26.6 percent from the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from 44 tractor makers show that in the first eight
months, these enterprises produced more than one million small
tractors, surging 16.1 percent in a year-on-year comparison.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
