<HEADLINE> Seminar on Auto Pollution Held in SW China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Experts from dozens of
countries and regions gathered recently in Kunming, capital of
southwest China's Yunnan Province, to discuss ways to tackle the
problem of auto emissions.
</P>
<P>
The week-long seminar, "the 99 International Car Pollution
Control Technique and Exhibition," was organized by the State
Environmental Protection Administration and opened Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the participants were over 100 automobile manufacturers
from Germany, France, the United States, Britain, Australia,
Sweden, and Italy, as well as Sino-foreign joint ventures and car
producers from other parts of China.
</P>
<P>
Auto-emission pollution has become a major source of pollution
in large Chinese cities including Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province. More than half of the
air pollution in the larger cities is caused by automobile
emissions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
