<HEADLINE> China's Oldest Symphony Orchestra Celebrates 120th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Symphony
Orchestra, China's oldest philharmonic, staged a series of
activities recently to celebrate the 120th anniversary of its
birth.
</P>
<P>
These events, including a concert, a forum and an exhibition,
have attracted hundreds of well-known Chinese and foreign
musicians.
</P>
<P>
The much-feted symphony orchestra evolved out of the Shanghai
Public Band, which was established in 1879.
</P>
<P>
Since 1949, the year new China was founded, it has performed
more than 3,000 concerts in more than 10 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the symphony gave a record 121 performances to
audiences totaling 120,000 people from China and abroad.  
</P>
