<HEADLINE> Ecuadorian President Reshuffles Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadorian President Jamil Mahuad
on Thursday reshuffled the cabinet, moving Javier Espinoza from
the post of Secretary of State for Production to Secretary of
State for Economy, replacing Guillermo Lasso.
</P>
<P>
Lasso resigned two weeks ago reportedly because of his
disagreements with President Mahuad and former Finance Minister
Ana Lucia Armijos in the handling of Brady bonds.
</P>
<P>
On September 30, Ecuador became the first country to default on
Brady bonds, as it had been facing its worst economic crisis in
decades. But Lasso was opposed to a moratorium on the payment in
Brady bonds.
</P>
<P>
Brady bonds, named after former U.S. Treasury Secretary
Nicholas Brady, were created in 1989 to refinance the debt burden
of developing nations.
</P>
<P>
Juaqn Falconi Puig was named as the new Secretary of State for
Production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
