<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0356 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Return of Macao to End China's History of Humiliation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Ma Kwok temple is the
oldest building in Macao and the place where Portuguese
colonialists first touched the ground of the island 446 years ago.
</P>
<P>
With the clicking of the clock nearing the new millennium,
Macao is also waiting for its return to the motherland, thus
ending China's humiliating history of foreign occupation of its
territory.
</P>
<P>
History records that Chinese have lived on this island for 6,
000 years, and when the Qin Dynasty united China in 212 B.C., it
was included as a part of China's territory.
</P>
<P>
In 1535, the Ming Dynasty moved its trade commission to Macao
to regulate monopolized foreign trade business there.
</P>
<P>
The 16th century was also the prime for Portugal's push toward
the global expansion of colonialism. After many of China's
coastal regions, the colonialists trained their eyes on Macao.
</P>
<P>
Unlike the armed robbery of Hong Kong by the British, the
Portuguese relied solely on fraud and bribery to take over Macao.
</P>
<P>
In 1553, some Portuguese pretended that their cargo ship had
hit rocks and asked for places in Macao to have their goods dried
in the sun.
</P>
<P>
With some bribery to local government officials, they obtained
permits to stay on the island, and much more followed to form
their own Portuguese town.
</P>
<P>
The central government of the Ming Dynasty still exercised
sovereignty rights over Macao, and along with collecting tax and
rents, it also garrisoned troops there and issued a law banning
piracy in the island.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0357 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Stresses Kosovo's Status of Autonomous Province of Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 14 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan said in Pristina on Thursday that Kosovo is not an
independent state but an autonomous province of the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference in capital city of Kosovo, Annan
said the U.N. Resolution 1244 has prescribed Kosovo as an
autonomous province within Yugoslavia. This expresses his clear
stance on the issue, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The secretary-general, who arrived in Pristina Wednesday on a
two-day trip to the war-shattered province, expressed deep regrets
over the death of Valentin Krumov of Bulgaria, a U.N. staffer who
was killed Monday night by ethnic Albanian teenagers mistaking him
as a Serb.
</P>
<P>
He promised to take all possible measures to prevent the
reoccurrence of similar tragedies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
