</P>
<P>
-- China successfully put its Earth Resources Satellite, the ZY-
1, into the orbit yesterday with a Chinese Long March 4-B rocket
that blasted off at 11:16 am (Beijing time) from the Taiyuan
Launching Center in North China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, a joint production of China and Brazil, is
designed to gather terrestrial information on the environment,
agriculture and urban planning.
</P>
<P>
