and will be forced to wear a cast. He averaged 19.9 points, 5.3
rebounds and 3.8 assists last season for Los Angeles, which was
beaten by the eventual champion San Antonio Spurs in the Western
Conference semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately for the Lakers, they signed shooting guard Ron
Harper on Wednesday and his veteran presence should help offset
the loss of Bryant.
</P>
