<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Pakistani English newspapers Friday.
</P>
<P>
The News:
</P>
<P>
-- Putting Pakistan under military rule by imposing emergency,
Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff Committee General Pervaiz
Musharraf assumed the office of chief executive with sweeping
powers, keeping the constitution in abeyance and suspending the
country's legislature at all levels. The sate affairs will now be
run under the Provisional Constitution Order.
</P>
<P>
-- A day before the National Assembly was scheduled to meet,
the troops evacuated the staff of the National Assembly
Secretariat and the Senate from the Parliament House Thursday and
took control of the entire building.
</P>
<P>
The Nation:
</P>
<P>
-- A case will be registered against deposed Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif, his personal secretary Saeed Mehdi, Shahid Khaqan
Abbasi and former police chief of Sindh province for plotting to
eliminate General Pervaiz Musharraf, chairman of the Joint Chiefs
of Staff Committee and chief of the Army Staff.
</P>
<P>
The Frontier Post:
</P>
<P>
-- Deposed Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, being held under house
arrest, has been transferred to a new location in Lahore by army
authorities, military sources said Thursday. 
</P>
