<HEADLINE> International Symposium on Ecological Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A five-day international
symposium on planning and management of ecological environment is
being held in Haikou, capital of south China's Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, 86 Chinese and overseas specialists,
as well as representatives from international organizations
attended the symposium which will be closed Sunday.
</P>
<P>
During the symposium, participants from the United States,
Canada, Germany, Britain, Switzerland, Italy, Denmark, Spain,
China and other countries discuss theories and ways of planning
and management concerning ecological construction, urban and
regional environment, and exchange experiences and latest
achievements in this regard.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has attached close attention to the
protection of ecological environment, which is now China's
fundamental state policy and the country is working hard to
implement the strategy of sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
A total of 111 counties, cities and districts in the country,
as well as Hainan Province are designated as ecological
demonstration places. Special teams have sent to inspect some of
them and found great progress in ecological development in those
areas.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is sponsored by the Hainan Provincial Bureau of
Land, Marine and Environmental Resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
