<HEADLINE> "Beauty and the Beast" in Chinese to Play in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Performed by a cast of Chinese
actors and actresses in Chinese, the famous American Disney
musical "Beauty and the Beast" will be presented at the Beijing
Theater on October 22.
</P>
<P>
The performance is directed by Asari Keita, whose Japanese
opera troupe worked with the Disney Studio in 1995 to stage the
musical in Tokyo for 28 months, and then on tour around the rest
of Japan. The troupe is providing costumes, properties and a sound
system for the Chinese production.
</P>
<P>
The cast of about 40 was selected from among young singers and
dancers throughout China. They have been to Japan to receive
special training for this staging, and director Asari Keita
believes their performance has reached world-class levels.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Theater has undergone 2 months of renovation to
accommodate this large-scale musical production.
</P>
<P>
The show has been adapted from the cartoon musical "Beauty and
the Beast" originally produced by the Disney Studio in 1994. It
has had a record 6-year run on Broadway in New York City, and has
attracted audiences all around the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
