<HEADLINE> Lakers Sign Bulls' Veteran Guard Ron Harper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Phil Jackson has succeeded
in bringing one of his former players to the Los Angeles Lakers on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers have signed Ron Harper to a two-year, 4.2 million U.
S. dollars contract, re-uniting the veteran guard with the coach
for whom he helped win three NBA championships as a member of the
Chicago Bulls.
</P>
<P>
A 13-year NBA veteran, the last five seasons spent as a member
of the Bulls, Harper owns career averages of 14.8 points, 4.3
rebounds and 4.0 assists. He averaged 11.2 points, 5.1 rebounds
and 3.3 assists during the 1999 campaign for the Bulls.
</P>
<P>
"We're pleased to add a player of Ron Harper's ability to our
team," said Lakers vice president of basketball operations Jerry
West.
</P>
<P>
"I'm happy to be here and happy to be a part of this great team
that is hopefully going to be even greater very soon," Harper said.
</P>
<P>
Harper started in the backcourt along with Michael Jordan as
the Bulls won titles in 1996, 1997 and 1998. Jordan retired
following the 1997-98 campaign and Jackson took a year off before
assuming control of the Lakers in June.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers suffered an 88-84 loss to the Washington Wizards in
their exhibition opener on Wednesday night as Jackson attempted to
install the triangle offense that allowed the Bulls to win six NBA
crowns this decade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
