<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Confucius Website Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The world's first website devoted
to Confucius, China's ancient thinker and educator, is now on the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
Six sections, including an introduction to the life of
Confucius, Confucian works, and well-known remarks of Confucius,
can be accessed at: http://www.china kongzi.com.
</P>
<P>
The site is co-sponsored by the government of Qufu City and the
telecommunications bureau of Jining City in east China's Shandong
Province, where Confucius was born and lived.
</P>
<P>
The new site is part of a program to celebrate the 2,550th
anniversary of Confucius' birth.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition on Confucius has also opened in Qufu recently and
will remain open permanently.
</P>
<P>
Confucius (551 B.C.- 479 B.C.) is regarded as one of China's
greatest thinkers and educators, and the Confucian school of
thought that developed from his ideas has had a great influence on
China's political, cultural and social life for thousands of years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
