<HEADLINE> Life Normal in Pakistan after Enforcement of Emergency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan was calm and life
was normal in the capital as a state of emergency was enforced in
the country on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Government and private offices opened as routine and people
were busy in routine work.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rush was seen outside newspapers' stalls and the general
public was keen to read newspapers.
</P>
<P>
Most of the people were asleep when coup leader General Pervaiz
Musharraf declared the state of emergency and suspended the
constitution in the wee hours of Friday.
</P>
<P>
There has been some slight increase in the number of troops
outside key installations, including the parliament building. The
army personnel sealed off the building Thursday and staff of the
National Assembly and Senate evacuated.
</P>
<P>
No immediate comments available from political parties on the
declaration of emergency. However, the international TV channels
are showing interviews of people welcoming the army takeover.
</P>
</TEXT>
