<HEADLINE> Tianjin Reports Better Industrial Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, the leading industrial
center of north China, gained an industrial output value of 164.1
billion yuan in the first three quarters of this year, up 15.5
percent over the figure a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The sales rate for manufactured goods increased by one percent
to reach 97.6 percent in the first nine months, and profits of
paying concerns rose by 16 percent, while the amount of losses
incurred by deficit enterprises declined by 6.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
A municipal government official attributed the increased
industrial output to the development of new products and the
absorption of foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the city developed more than 2,000 new products
which contributed 22.5 percent to the city's total industrial
output value.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has given approval for foreign companies to form joint
ventures with 600 local state-owned enterprises, and this has led
to the influx of 4 billion U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
