<HEADLINE> National Library Extends Evening Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua)-- The National Library in Beijing
will extend evening service to 9 pm beginning next Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the director of the library, the nation's largest,
the library will provide twelve hours of daily service from 9 am
to 9 pm, except Saturdays and Sundays.
</P>
<P>
"Some reading rooms, including Chinese Social Science
Periodicals and the Electronic Reading Room, are among the first
to institute the new hours," he said, adding that he hopes this
will satisfy readers' needs, especially those who have tight
schedules during the day.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time the National Library has extended its
hours and opened more reading areas at night since it moved into
the new building in 1987.  
</P>
