<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0432 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Up to 40% of Imported Goods in Russia Illegal:Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, October 15 (Xinhua) -- About 30-40 percent of imported
goods in Russia are smuggled from abroad, causing great losses to
state customs earnings, said a top Russian customs official Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mikhail Vanin, chairman of the State Customs Committee (SCC),
told Izvesta daily that the SCC has collected 125 billion rubles (
around 5 billion U.S. dollars) in the first nine months of 1999,
well below the planned index because Russia's import was far less
than it had been predicted by the Economy Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Russia forecast it was to import some 28 billion
dollars of goods this year, but actually, the imports will be only
21 billion dollars, said the official.
</P>
<P>
Vanin attributed the surge of illegal imports to the
ineffective implementation of tariff policies and the uncontrolled
influx of duty-free humanitarian aid.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
