<HEADLINE> Guoxin Securities Given Approval to Add Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The China Securities
Regulatory Commission has approved one of its leading stock
brokerage company's plan to raise its registered capital from 800
million yuan to one billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
With this action, more state-owned enterprises will be able to
enter the country's stock market, and the approval demonstrates
the improvement of Guoxin Securities Co. Ltd.'s economic strength.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time Guoxin Securities will add to its
capital. In 1997, the company raised its assets from 100 million
yuan to 800 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The company has six shareholders including the Shenzhen
International Trust Company, the Shenzhen Investment Management
Company, the Shenzhen Airports Co. Ltd., the Hongta Industrial Co.
Ltd., a well-known cigarette maker in Yunnan Province, the First
Automobile Group Corporation in northeast China's Jilin Province,
and the Beijing Urban Construction Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Guoxin Securities has acted as the leading underwriter for
issuing shares of over 80 enterprises and has made recommendations
for the listings. It has also underwritten issues of state
treasury bonds and corporate bonds of large enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The company has realized well over 400 million yuan in profits
annually since 1996.  
</P>
