Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji attended the two-day meeting on
Thursday and delivered an important speech.
</P>
<P>
Also on Thursday, Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing hosted a
banquet in the Great Hall of the People to entertain the
participants.
</P>
<P>
The Asia-Europe Meeting is a cooperative mechanism aimed at
enhancing contacts between the two continents.
</P>
<P>
It consists of 10 Asian and 15 European countries: Austria,
Belgium, Brunei, China, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Greece
Indonesia, Ireland, Italy, Japan, the Republic of Korea,
Luxembourg, Malaysia, the Netherlands, the Philippines, Portugal,
Singapore, Spain, Sweden, Thailand, the United Kingdom and Viet
Nam, as well as representatives from the Commission of the
European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
