<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EDS: Updates with details, more infomration mee101503hke -- Israel Releases 151 Palestinian Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Israel released Friday morning
151 Palestinian security prisoners under the Sharm el-Sheikh peace
deal signed in Septemer.
</P>
<P>
Buses loaded with the prisoners left Nafha prison near Mitzeh
Ramon and Shikma prison near Ashkelon at about 4:00 am local time
(0200 GMT) and traveled to different locations between Israel and
the Palestinian territories as agreed by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 151 Palestinian prisoners were released from those
two prisons and others were selected from other lockups in Israel.
</P>
<P>
The prisoners were handed over to the Palestinian side at
checkpoints near Tulkarm, Ramallah, Hebron and Gaza.
</P>
<P>
Among the 151 prisoners being released, 44 were involved in
attacks that led to light injuries of Israeli citizens, 42 from
other Arab countries, 38 murdered suspected Arab collaborators with
Israel and others were imprisoned for various other offenses, Israel
said.
</P>
<P>
The list of the prisoners released Friday also included 10
members of the Islamic Militant Resistance Movement (Hamas) and
Islamic Jihad (freedom fighters) and five of them from Jordan.
</P>
<P>
This was the second group of Palestinian prisoners being released
by israel. Israel freed the first batch of 199 on September 9.
</P>
<P>
Friday's release came a week later than scheduled due to a
dispute between Israeli and Palestinian negotiators over the list of
prisoners. Israel refuses to free Palestinians who killed Israelis
or who were arrested for attacking Israelis after Israel and
Palestinians began signing interim peace accords in 1993.
</P>
<P>
For the Palestinians, the issue of the prisoners remaining in
Israel jails is one of the most sensitive and emotional in the peace
process - almost every Palestinian family has had at least one
member in an Israeli prison.
</P>
<P>
Mahane Ofer near Ramallah in the West Bank was one of the
crossings where the Palestinian prisoners were dropped, as a large
group of Palestinians were waiting to meet their beloved ones
coming home.
</P>
<P>
"I have been waiting for 15 years for my son to come home and
thank Allah my son is going out from Israeli jail today,"
61-year-old Aziz told Xinhua, while waiting for the buses loaded
with the prisoners to come.
</P>
<P>
The prisoner release is part of the implementation of the Sharm
el-Sheikh peace deal and Israel will free another group of
Palestinian prisoners by the end of the year ahead of the Muslim
holy month of Ramadan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
