<HEADLINE> Fresh Fighting Kills at Least 48 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Defense Ministry
said Friday that at least 48 Tamil rebels and government soldiers
were killed in the fresh fighting in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry said in a statement that troops on
Thursday killed over 30 guerrillas of the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) with artillery in a retaliatory counter attack
east of Ampakamam in the Wanni region.
</P>
<P>
It said 15 security force personnel were killed and 61 others
were injured mainly due to the rebel's mortar fire.
</P>
<P>
Three other LTTE rebels were killed in two separate incidents
in the Jaffna region, it added.
</P>
<P>
The official evening newspaper The Observer reported Friday
that the navy destroyed two LTTE boats and sank one Thursday night
in a sea battle in south of Kokilai, about 270 kilometers
northeast of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a 16-year-old war against
the government to demand a separate homeland for minority Tamils
in Sri Lanka's north and east. 
</P>
</TEXT>
