<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0456 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 die, 20,000 Families Homeless in Floods in S.Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- At least two persons died and
20,000 families were rendered homeless following floods resulting
from incessant thundershowers for over a week in Sri Lanka,
officials said Friday.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Department of Social Services said the two
were killed in landslides at Ayagama in the Ratnapura district in
southwestern Sri Lanka and the homeless families were mostly in
the coastal belt of the country.
</P>
<P>
In Colombo district alone, around 10,000 families have been
displaced, local officials said, adding that the worst affected
areas are along the western coastal belt, from Wennappuwa to
Puttalam.
</P>
<P>
Displaced families have been given refuge in schools and other
community halls and are provided with cooked meals and dry
rations. A sum of 10,000 rupees (140 U.S. dollars) will be given
to each homeless family.
</P>
<P>
The floods caused by the rains have inundated many main roads
and by-roads in many parts of the country, and many people were
forced to report to duty late or stay at home, officials said.
</P>
<P>
According to the Meteorological Department, Thursday's
thunderstorm and gusty winds and accompanying rains were due to
atmospheric disturbances over Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
It added that spells of heavy rains can be expected during the
current active monsoon season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
