<HEADLINE> Development Zone with Clean Environment Attracts Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A clean environment has helped
the Weihai Economic and Technological Development Zone in east
China's Shandong Province draw increasing numbers of overseas
investors.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics indicate that investors from dozens of other
countries and regions, including the Republic of Korea, the United
States, Japan and Singapore, have opened some 300 businesses in
the zone, with contractual overseas investments of 690 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Of the overseas-funded businesses, more than half have
increased their investment in the zone over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Many overseas investors say the clean environment is conducive
to ensuring product quality.
</P>
<P>
Since it was established seven years ago, the zone has given
top priority to environmental protection and used 260 million yuan
for pollution control.
</P>
<P>
The zone has turned down 75 investment projects that were
potential polluters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
