<BODY>
<HEADLINE> DPRK Disapproves of Multilateral Cooperation System in Northeast Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Foreign
Ministry of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) said
here Thursday that the DPRK "disapproves of the construction of a
multilateral peace and cooperation system in Northeast Asia" and "
does not allow the Korea issue to become the topic of any
discussions."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman made the statement in an interview with the
Korean Central News Agency amid foreign media reports that the U.S.
, Japan and South Korea are planning to meet in Cheju-do in South
Korea later this month to discuss the establishment of a
multilateral peace and cooperation system in Northeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that DPRK thinks it is too early to consider
establishing such a multilateral peace and cooperation system in
Northeast Asia, because there is no such a relationship between
the DPRK and some of its neighboring countries which can enable
them to cooperate with respect to issues of "national security".
</P>
<P>
He stressed that in order to ease the tension on the Korean
Peninsula, the U.S. government must withdraw its troops from the
peninsula and sign peace agreements with the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
"The reunification of the Korean Peninsula is a matter of the
Korean people," the spokesman said, adding that the reunification
should be realized through peace talks between the two sides on
the Korean Peninsula independently.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0467 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Forex Reserves Top 151.5 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China, the
central bank of the country, announced today that China's foreign
exchange reserves reached 151.51 billion U.S. dollars at the end
of September, an increase of 6.55 billion U.S. dollars from at the
end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The financial report released today by the central bank
indicates that in the first three quarters this year, China's
financial sector maintained smooth operation, and the total money
supply was basically appropriate.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that at the end of September, the outstanding
amount of broad money (M2) exceeded 11.5 trillion yuan, up 15.3
percent from the same period last year; the outstanding amount of
narrow money (M1) stood at 4.19 trillion yuan, up 14.8 percent;
and the outstanding amount of money in circulation (M0) was 1.22
trillion yuan, up 16.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Cash supply in the first nine months was more than 105 billion
yuan, an increase of more than 70 billion yuan on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
At the end of September, the aggregate outstanding amount of
deposits stood at 10.55 trillion yuan, up 14.8 percent year on
year. Of the total residents' savings accounted for 5.93 trillion
yuan, up 15.1 percent; and corporate savings increased 13 percent
to 3.48 trillion yuan.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the aggregate outstanding amount of loans was
9.33 trillion yuan, up 13 percent. The first three quarters saw an
increase in loans by more than 700 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
At the end of September, the exchange rate was 8.2775 yuan to
one U.S. dollar, showing a slight appreciation for the yuan
compared with the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman said that in the last quarter of this year,
the central bank will give further play to the role of monetary
policies, improve financial services, and appropriately increase
the money supply in a bid to support the reform and development of
state-owned enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
