<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Brazilian Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo,
in a meeting here today with visiting Brazilian Minister of
Science and Technology Ronaldo Sardenberg, said that Sino-
Brazilian cooperation in space technology will play a positive
role in the development of this endeavor in both countries.
</P>
<P>
Wu extended his congratulations on the successful launching of
the Earth Resources Satellite, the ZY-1, a joint production of
China and Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Sardenberg expressed his thanks for the Chinese government's
support of bilateral cooperation in the field of space.
</P>
<P>
He said that Brazil would like to cement its cooperation ties
with China in the area of high technology.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, which was put into orbit on Thursday, is
designed to gather terrestrial information on the environment,
agriculture, and urban planning.
</P>
<P>
The ZY-1 satellite weighs 1,540 kilograms and is expected to
function for about two years.
</P>
<P>
While in operation, the satellite will provide remote sensing
images and data to China, Brazil and other countries with the
ability to receive them.  
</P>
