<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0474 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Releases 151 Palestinian Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Israel released Friday
morning 151 Palestinian security prisoners under the Sharm
el-Sheikh peace deal signed in September.
</P>
<P>
Buses loaded with the prisoners left Nafha prison near Mitzeh
Ramon and Shikma prison near Ashkelon at about 4:00 am local time
(0200 GMT) and traveled to different locations between Israel and
the Palestinian territories as agreed by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 151 Palestinian prisoners were released from those
two prisoners and others were selected from other lockups in
Israel.
</P>
<P>
The prisoners were handed over to the Palestinian side at
checkpoints near Tulkarm, Ramallah, Hebron and Gaza.
</P>
<P>
Among the 151 prisoners being released, 44 were involved in
attacks that led to light injuries of Israeli citizens, 42 from
other Arab countries, 38 murdered suspected Arab collaborated 10
members of the Islamic Militant Resistance Movement (Hamas) and
Islamic Jihad (freedom fighters) and five of them from Jordan.
</P>
<P>
This was the second group of Palestinian prisoners being
released by Israel. Israel released the first batch of 199 on
September 9.
</P>
<P>
Friday's release came a week later than scheduled due to a
dispute between Israeli and Palestinian negotiators over the list
of prisoners. Isreal refuses to free Palestinians who killed
Israelis or who were arrested for attacking Israelis after Israel
and Palestinians began signing interim peace accords in 1993.
</P>
<P>
For the Palestinians, the issue of the prisoners remaining in
Israeli jails is one of the most sensitive and emotional in the
peace process - almost every Palestinian family has had at least
one member in an Israeli prison.
</P>
<P>
Mahane Ofer near Ramallah is one of the crossings where the
Palestinian prisoners were freed Friday.
</P>
<P>
A large group of Palestinians were waiting there to meet their
beloved ones coming home.
</P>
<P>
"I have been waiting for 15 years for my son to come home and
thank Allah my son is going out from Israeli jail today,"
61-year-old Aziz told Xinhua, while waiting for the buses loaded
with the prisoners to come.
</P>
<P>
The prisoner release is part of the implementation of the
Sharm el-Sheikh peace deal and Israel will free another group of
Palestinian prisoners by the end of the year ahead the Muslim's
holy month of Ramadan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
