<HEADLINE> Angola Expresses Condolences on Death of Nyerere </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Angolan Foreign Minister Joao
Miranda has expressed his profound condolences on the death of
Tanzania's former President Julius Nyerere, official news agency
Angop reported here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to his Tanzanian counterpart, Miranda said that it
gave him much pain to learn of the sad news on the physical
pass-away of the ex- president of Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
"We fell into profound grief and consternation when we heard
the death of Nyerere, founder of the Tanzanian nation," said the
letter issued by the Angolan Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The note also said that "at this moment of profound pain and
mourning," the Angolan people and government join together with
all Tanzanians and express the most sorrowful condolence to the
family of the first president of the east African country since
its independence.
</P>
<P>
Julius Nyerere, 77, died of leukemia Thursday in London.
</P>
