<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quality of Chinese-Made Home Appliances Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese-made household
electronic appliances are of good quality and most of the products
from China's large enterprises are up to national standards,
according to the State Quality and Technical Supervision
Administration.
</P>
<P>
The administration conducted a selective examination of 1,742
products made by 1,598 enterprises across China from July to
September, and about 79 percent of them reached national standards.
</P>
<P>
The examination shows that Chinese household appliances as a
whole are up to standard, with the rate for washing machines,
refrigerators, microwave ovens and range hood reaching 96 percent,
94 percent, 92 percent and 77 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Currently, China is the world's largest producer of washing
machines and microwave ovens. The annual output of washing
machines exceeds 10 million sets, and that of microwave ovens is
expected to reach eight million this year.
</P>
<P>
The quality of many Chinese-made home appliances is near or
equal to that of similar products in other countries, but the
prices for Chinese products are much lower.
</P>
<P>
The examination also indicates that 97 percent of the products
made by large enterprises met national standards, 13.6 and 27
percentage points higher than the products of medium-sized and
small enterprises, respectively. The exam also shows that state-
owned enterprises manufacture better quality products than private
enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
