<HEADLINE> China Development Bank Opens Hong Kong Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China Development Bank (CDB)
officially launched the opening of its Hong Kong representative
office Friday as a step to enhance cooperation with foreign
financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
Approved by the People's Bank of China and the Hong Kong
Monetary Authority, the CDB Hong Kong office will provide liaison
services for its head office in such business areas as bond issue,
syndicate borrowing, foreign exchange settlements and investment
banking business.
</P>
<P>
CDB is a policy lending bank established in 1994 by the Chinese
government to strengthen infrastructure construction and set up
mechanisms of investment risk control. With 50 billion yuan (6.02
billion U.S. dollars) of equity capital, the bank mainly provides
medium and long-term fixed asset loans.
</P>
<P>
CDB has so far established agent relationship with more than 80
foreign banks, 70 percent of which have established branches or
representative offices in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In this connection, the establishment of CDB Hong Kong office
will facilitate the bank's timely obtaining international
financial information, and utilizing international markets as a
means of financing China's economic development, according to
economists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
