<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks End Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong stocks plunged
187.74 points or 1.50 percent Friday to finish the week at 12,299.
08.
</P>
<P>
The turnover also fell to 7.907 billion HK dollars (1.014
billion U.S. dollars), sharply down 5.251 billion HK dollars (673
million U.S. dollars) from the 13.158 billion HK dollars (1.687
billion U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Traders attributed the fall to negative impact of the comment
made by U.S Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan that he was
worried about the potential bubble in Wall Street stock prices.
</P>
<P>
Sub-indices of Finance, Utilities, Properties and Commerce and
Industry all went down by 1.62 percent, 1.42 percent, 1.86 percent
and 1.13 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 4.23 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corporations Index down 3.56 percent.
</P>
<P>
Compared to last week, the Hang Seng Index fell 813.34 points
or 6.20 percent this week. The stock market only managed to inch
up 10.95 points Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong stocks opened lower Friday with the blue chips
down 0.67 points or 0.01 percent at 12,486.15.
</P>
<P>
The stock prices decreased 88.53 points or 0.71 percent to
close the morning session at 12,398.29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
