<HEADLINE> Bronze Festival Held in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The '99 China Bronze Festival was
held recently by east China's Anhui provincial government in
Tongling in the southern part of the province, which is birthplace
of bronze culture in China with a 3,000-year history of producing
bronze.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of merchants from Europe, America, Southeast Asia,
Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan and the mainland participated in the 3-
day event.
</P>
<P>
A series of trade fairs, business talks, and exhibitions of
bronze products were staged during the festival.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-three universities and research institutes from Beijing,
Shanghai and Hefei signed 25 contracts with several firms, and 8
of the contracts were signed with foreign dealers worth 13.59
million US dollars, including 10.98 million US dollars of direct
investment. Seven domestic cooperation projects worth 400 million
yuan (48 million US dollars) were signed, including purchase and
sale contracts worth 15 million yuan (1.8 million US dollars).
</P>
