<HEADLINE> ADB Launches 1b-U.S.-Dollar Global Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
launched a one-billion-U.S.-dollar global bond issue on Thursday,
the bank said Friday in a news release.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said the bonds have a coupon rate of 6.5 percent per
annum payable semi-annually and a three-year straight maturity.
</P>
<P>
According to the ADB, the proceeds of the issue will be part of
the ADB's ordinary capital resources and used in its ordinary
(non-concessional) lending operations.
</P>
<P>
This is ADB's second global bond issue in 1999. In April, the
bank launched a five-year 1.25-billion-U.S.-dollar global bond
issue. 
