<HEADLINE> Finnish FM Stresses Right EU Policy On Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAMPERE, Finland, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Finnish Foreign
Minister Tarja Halonen said here Friday that the European Union (
EU) leaders need to reach long-standing solutions on the asylum
system and on the fight against discrimination and racism.
</P>
<P>
The European Union is a community of shared values, human
rights among the guiding principles, Ms. Holonen told the European
Council on Refugees and Exiles, a meeting organized by some non-
governmental groups.
</P>
<P>
The Finnish foreign minister said she was particularly
concerned over the persecution and violence experienced by women.
Women and children make up a decisive but too often an invisible
majority of the world's refugee population. "Their special needs
have to be addressed," she added.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the distinction between the two phenomena, asylum
and migration, Halonen said Europe's migration policy must be
based on respect for human rights and the right to seek and enjoy
asylum has to be safeguarded.
</P>
<P>
The European Union is working towards this goal, she added.
</P>
