<HEADLINE> HK Outlines Future Vision for Victoria Harbor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Town Planning
Board Friday pledged to work hard to make the Victoria Harbor
attractive, vibrant, accessible and symbolic of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Announcing its finalized vision statement for the Victoria
Harbor, a spokesman for the board said the vision and goals will
serve as a basis for the formulation of long-term planning
strategies to guide the future planning of the harbor and the
waterfront areas.
</P>
<P>
The plan, which was put out for consultation earlier this year,
received warm support from the public.
</P>
<P>
"To take account of the public views received, the board has
refined the wording of the statement of intent on reclamation to
clearly specify that 'the harbor is to be protected and preserved
as a special public asset and a natural heritage of the people of
Hong Kong'," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"Reclamation in the harbor should only be carried out to meet
essential community needs and public aspirations," the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
"It has to be environmentally acceptable and compatible with
the principle of sustainable development and the principle of
presumption against reclamation in the harbor," the spokesman
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
