<HEADLINE> Finland, EU Express Condolences On Nyerere's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAMPERE, Finland, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Finnish President and
Current European Union (EU) president Martti Ahtisaari expressed "
great regret" over the death of former Tanzanian President Julius
Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of Finland and the European Union, Ahtisaari in a
statement expressed his "heartfelt condolences to the family of
Mwalimu (teacher) Nyerere and the people of Tanzania on this sad
moment of their great loss," the Finnish news agency reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
"Tanzania has lost its founding father, a great leader and
teacher, whose spiritual legacy will remain a uniting force and
source of inspiration and stability in Tanzania," the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere's advice was sought through decades both in regional
and international affairs, Ahtisaari said. "His demise is a
personal loss for me," added the Finnish president, who is here
attending a special EU summit.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere, 77, died of chronic lymphocytic leukemia Thursday
morning at St. Thomas' Hospital in London.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere led the then Tanganyika to independence from Britain in
1961 and masterminded its union with Zanzibar in 1964 to form
Tanzania. Agfer leading the African country for 24 years, he
retired from his president post in 1985. 
</P>
</TEXT>
