<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Road Mishap in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A woman and her grandson were
killed in a road accident Friday in the district town of
Brahmanbaria, 84 kilometers northeast of here, the BSS news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred in the morning when a high-speeding
tractor coming from the southern side of the town hit a rickshaw
from behind, police and eyewitnesses said.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Prodip, eight, fell down from the rickshaw onto
the road and the tractor crushed over him, while his grandmother,
Chamely, 45, was injured seriously and died on way to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The angry people nearby set fire to the killer tractor, the BSS
said.
</P>
<P>
The local fire brigade rushed to the spot and tried to control
the fire, but was chased away by the angry mob. Later, local
police rushed to the scene and brought the situation under
control. 
</P>
