<HEADLINE> EU Parliament President Urges European Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAMPERE, Finland, October 15 (Xinhua) -- European Parliament
President Nicole Fontaine said here Friday that the European Union
(EU) must innovate in order to make Europe more comprehensible to
its citizens.
</P>
<P>
Giving a speech at a special European Union (EU) summit which
started here today, Fontaine said the creation of an area of "
freedom, security and justice" will provide an opportunity for
Europe to restore "public support for the ideal of European
integration".
</P>
<P>
Fontaine called on the heads of state of the 15-member EU to
lay foundations for a "qualitative step forward" through EU
leaders' political will.
</P>
<P>
It is the responsibility of the EU "to convince our fellow
citizens that the Union is genuinely capable of turning these
approaches into practical action," she said.
</P>
<P>
The EU parliament president admits that this is not a easy task,
but she believes that it is necessary to solve the "problems by
means of innovative approaches".
</P>
<P>
Referring to a EU Charter of Fundamental Rights to be signed by
the leaders at the summit, Fontaine said the agreement is "
essential in order to ensure that it is not treated exclusively as
a security policy", and in this connection, she would endorse the
position of the European Commission led by President Romano Prodi.
</P>
