<HEADLINE> General Musharraf Has Meeting With Army Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of Pakistan
General Pervaiz Musharraf Friday morning presided over a special
meeting of senior army officers in Rawalpindi, the twin city of
Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
The moot, attended by all corps commanders and principal staff
officers, reviewed issues of national importance, including the
prevailing situation in the country, and operational preparedness
following the imposition of emergency, said the Associated Press
of Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
Appreciating the unity and institutional solidarity displayed
by the armed forces, Musharraf apprised the participants of the
circumstances that had led to the imposition of emergency in the
country early Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
He discussed with them the measures which are being finalized
for the establishment of an efficient and impartial interim
set-up, according to APP.
</P>
<P>
Musharraf said that top priority will be accorded to economic
revival to ensure national integration and good governance.
</P>
<P>
He added that once all details were finalized, he would address
the nation taking them into confidence in this regard, according
to APP.
</P>
<P>
General Musharraf, who is also chairman of the Joint Chief of
Staff Committee and army chief of Pakistan, announced the
enforcement of a state of emergency and assumed the post of chief
executive of the post-coup country in the wee hours of Friday.
</P>
