<HEADLINE> International Symposium on Crime Prevention Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua)-- The International Symposium on
Crime Prevention, sponsored jointly by the Chinese People's
Security University and the Chinese Society of Criminology, opened
here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Entao, assistant minister of Public Security, delivered a
speech at the opening ceremony, saying that at the threshold of
the new century, crime prevention is drawing more and more
attention from governments and scholars around the world.
</P>
<P>
"During the past five decades, the Chinese government has
attached great importance to crime prevention, as a result, a
social security administration and crime prevention system with
Chinese characteristics has finally come into being," he said.
</P>
<P>
Sun Zhongguo, president of the Chinese People's Security
University, told the gathering that the global spread of crime has
made international exchange and cooperation on crime prevention
both necessary and important.
</P>
<P>
"The symposium, therefore, will offer a golden opportunity for
criminologists both at home and abroad, and will have active
impact on international crime prevention practices," he said.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 experts and scholars from across the world will
attend the four-day symposium, discussing such topics as strategy
of crime prevention, prevention of juvenile delinquency and
community policing. 
