<HEADLINE> EC Provides Grants to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
has decided to provide Nepal with a grant assistance of 300,000
euro (300,000 U.S. dollars) to refugee affected communities
through Rural Reconstruction Nepal (RRN).
</P>
<P>
EC and RRN have signed an agreement on implementing a
socio-economic development program for communities affected by
Bhutanese refugees in Jhapa and Morang districts in eastern Nepal.
</P>
<P>
EC will, for a period of three years, help implement the
program in selected areas of the two districts that are affected
by refugee camps.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the program is to mitigate the effects of
refugees on the socio-economic lives of local residents through
developing harmonious relationships among the communities and
implementing programs such as education and awareness, irrigation
development, income and employment generation and micro credit.
</P>
<P>
Rural Reconstruction Nepal is a non-governmental development
organization working in the field of people empowerment in rural
Nepal through implementation of various integrated development
programs. It is working in 10 districts through 15 different
programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
