<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0516 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Estrada to Personally Lead Charter Change Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada said Friday that he will personally lead the campaign to
inform the public about the benefits of the proposed
Constitutional Corrections for Development (Concord).
</P>
<P>
The president noted in a statement that a recent survey showed
that less than 18 percent of Filipinos are aware of the benefits
of the Concord-initiated economic reforms for the economy and
their daily life.
</P>
<P>
He expressed confidence that given the chance to fully
understand the advantages of his proposed economic reforms through
the Concord, the people would "vote overwhelmingly in favor of
this initiative."
</P>
<P>
The president has created the Cabinet Task Force Concord to
draw up and implement an advocacy plan aimed at informing the
people about the economic reforms through the Concord process.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said he will lead the launching of the Concord
information campaign next month with local government officials,
members of Congress, the business sector and non-government
organizations.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that it is the people who will decide the fate of
the Concord through a plebiscite, which will come after Congress
has deliberated on it and the Preparatory Commission on
Constitutional Reforms completes its task by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that to cope with population growth, bold
economic reforms proposed in the Concord are needed to enable the
government to meet the needs of the people.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said these economic reforms include the lifting of the
constitutional restrictions on the foreign ownership of land and
equity in key industries and the public utilities sector.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that he is starting his Concord campaign early
to give people enough time to study the Concord process and decide
on it before 200l, his target date for implementing these economic
reforms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
