<HEADLINE> HK's Golden Jubilee Together Delegation to Visit Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong delegation will
go to Beijing Saturday to present an album listing out names of
110 inland schools financed by Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
The project is part of the efforts initiated by the Golden
Jubilee Together Organizing Committee to commemorate the 50th
anniversary of the People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by David Lan, Secretary for Home Affairs of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, will include more
than 130 representatives of individuals and organizations, which
have donated money for building or renovating schools in remote
and impoverished areas of inland.
</P>
<P>
Bayin Chaolu, chairman of the China Youth Development
Foundation, will receive the album on behalf of the Central
Government at the presentation ceremony to be held at the Great
Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
The Golden Jubilee Together Organizing Committee was set up in
June this year by 15 Hong Kong personalities born in 1949, the
same year the People' Republic of China was established.
</P>
<P>
They share the dual objectives of mobilizing the community to
set up a permanent charity to provide emergency relief to disaster
victims and to coordinate the community's efforts to finance the
building of schools for needy children in the inland.
</P>
<P>
Since inauguration, the organizing committee has raised more
than 10 million HK dollars (1.3 million U.S. dollars) for the
Golden Jubilee Together Charity Foundation as emergency disaster
relief.
</P>
<P>
In addition, more than 22 million HK dollars (2.8 U.S. million
dollars) have been pledged by Hong Kong people for building and
reconstruction of schools for children in the remote parts of the
Chinese inland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
