<HEADLINE> Three Gang Members From Macao Sentenced to Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Zhuhai City Intermediate
People's Court today handed down death sentences for three
underworld gang members from Macao who were convicted of murder,
robbery, kidnapping, and gun trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The three criminals to be executed include the gang's leader Ye
Chengjian, who is from Hong Kong, and his two accomplices, He
Jingsheng and Li Xinwen. Twelve other members of the gang received
sentences ranging from death with reprieve, life imprisonment, and
other set terms of imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
The gang has committed a series of violent crimes in Macao and
the Chinese mainland over the past few years. On November 8, 1998,
the gang murdered a man whose family name was Wu in Zhuhai.
</P>
<P>
On November 12, 1994, the gang kidnapped two Taiwanese
businessman and demanded ransom of three million Taiwanese yuan
from their families.
</P>
<P>
On June 11, 1998, calling themselves police from Macao, the
gang broke into the home of a Zhuhai resident and took 500,000 U.S.
dollars and 840,000 Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
Ye's family members and about 250 people from all walks of life
in Zhuhai attended the public sentencing in court today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
