<HEADLINE> China Unicom Purchases Ericsson Mobile Telecom Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Sweden-based Ericsson announced
today that it has received a 54 million US dollar order for mobile
telecommunications systems from China Unicom.
</P>
<P>
According to the contracts, the Sichuan branch of China Unicom
will use the Ericsson-brand products to enlarge its capacity of
global system mobile telecommunications (GSM) at the third stage.
The systems will be delivered in December this year.
</P>
<P>
The systems will bring the number of China Unicom subscribers
in Sichuan Province to 680,000.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish company has signed nine contracts with China Unicom
for such mobile telecommunications systems this year, involving
180 million US dollars in total contractual value.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1994, China Unicom now has nearly three million
mobile phone subscribers, and is the second-largest cellular phone
service provider in the country.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, Ericsson has opened 32 offices and
eight joint ventures, and employed more than 3,800 Chinese in
China. 
</P>
