<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0530 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKMC Notes to Be Listed on the SEHK Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Mortgage
Corporation (HKMC)'s 20 billion-HK dollar (2.6 billion-U.S. dollar)
Note Issuance Program (NIP) will be listed and traded on the Stock
Exchange of Hong Kong (SEHK) on October 22.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by the Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA)
on Friday after it signed the Program, Agency and Operations
Agreement in respect of the NIP with the HKMC and Bermuda Trust (
Far East) Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The signing of the agreement marked the completion of the legal
documentation for the listing of HKMC's NIP on the SEHK.
</P>
<P>
The NIP's seven outstanding issues, with an aggregate issue
amount of 3.5 billion HK dollars (448.7 million U.S. dollars),
will be listed on the SEHK on the same day.
</P>
<P>
The HKMA also announced that the tender for the eighth issue of
2-year HKMC Notes will be held on October 27.
</P>
<P>
An amount of 500 million HK dollars (64.1 million U.S. dollars)
in HKMC Notes will be offered for settlement on October 28.
</P>
<P>
The 500 million-HK dollar (64.1 million-U.S. dollar) HKMC Notes
issue is the eighth tranche of the 20 billion-HK dollar (2.6
billion-U.S. dollar) HKMC Note Issuance Program in which the HKMA
acts as the arranger, custodian, agent and operator.
</P>
<P>
The HKMC Notes, which are denominated in units of 50,000 HK
dollars (6,410 U.S. dollars), will be cleared through the Central
Moneymarkets Unit (CMU).
</P>
<P>
The HKMC will use the proceeds to support its mortgage purchase
program.
</P>
<P>
The HKMC is the first corporation in Hong Kong to list and
trade its debt securities on the SEHK by public tender since the
listing of the Government's Exchange Fund Notes (EFN) on August 16.
</P>
<P>
The listing will further enhance the HKMC's fund-raising
capabilities by extending its investor base, which already covers
financial institutions and institutional investors, to include
retail investors.
</P>
<P>
The Stock Exchange will provide an efficient and convenient
platform for retail investors to invest and trade the NIP notes.
Ready access to the HKMC's high-quality fixed-income securities
will help them to diversify and balance their investment
portfolios. 
</P>
</TEXT>
