<HEADLINE> Lao National Assembly 4th Session Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The fourth ordinary session of
the fourth legislature of the Lao National Assembly ended in
Vientiane on Thursday after endorsing the socio-economic
development plan of the country, Lao official news agency KPL
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The session, which started on September 30, also endorsed the
country's state budget for the 1999-2000 fiscal year and amended
Article 22 of the Criminal Act on adultery and seven articles of
the law on the Bank of Laos.
</P>
<P>
The session, KPL said, considered and took decisions on a
number of important matters relating to the tasks of national
defense and development in line with the Lao People's
Revolutionary Party's policy on renovation.
</P>
<P>
The session heard reports from the People's Supreme Court, the
General Prosecutor's Office and the National Assembly on their
respective performance.
</P>
<P>
Lao President Khamtay Siphandone and other party and state
leaders attended the closing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
A closing statement of the session said that the session was
conducted at a time when the entire party and people were
implementing the resolution of the 9th plenary meeting of the Lao
People's Revolutionary Party Central Committee. This session has
strengthened efforts to overcome economic and financial
difficulties, and the drives for the monsoon rice harvest and
agricultural production, it said. 
</P>
