<HEADLINE> Ukraine Concerns Over Veto of CTBT by U.S. Senates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Ukrainian Foreign Ministry on
Friday voiced serious concerns over the refusal by the U.S. Senate
to ratify the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT).
</P>
<P>
A statement released by the ministry said that as a country
which has dismissed using nuclear weapons, Ukraine clearly knows
the importance of the treaty which is a crucial part to sustaining
world stability, Ukrainian Interfax news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry stressed that nuclear-capable countries must
assume the responsibility for enacting the treaty. They must make
efforts to insure that the treaty is ratified and takes effect in
the near future.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Senate voted 51-48 Wednesday to reject the CTBT. More
than 150 countries have signed the pact but it cannot go into
force unless all 44 nuclear-capable states, including the United
States, ratify it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
