<HEADLINE> Iraq, Indonesia Sign Minutes on Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Iraq and Indonesia on Friday
signed minutes of the 5th session of the Iraqi-Indonesian Joint
Committee for Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed by Iraqi Trade Minister Mohammad Mehdi
Salah and visiting Indonesian Trade and Industry Minister Rahardi
Ramelan who arrived here on Tuesday evening with a large trade
delegation.
</P>
<P>
The two countries agreed on holding the 6th session of the
joint committee in Jakarta, capital of Indonesia, next year and
expanding Indonesian firms' participation in the Baghdad
International Fair due next month, the Iraqi News Agency reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the minutes, the two countries will exchange
expertises and Indonesia will provide training chances for Iraqi
personnel.
</P>
<P>
Ramelan told reporters on Wednesday that Indonesia had made
enlarged contacts with Iraq to develop southern Iraq's Toba and
Alaal oil fields whose daily production after operation is
estimated at 80,000 barrels.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian minister said that an oil delegation will
arrive in Baghdad in the next two weeks to continue discussions
with the Iraqi side.
</P>
<P>
Ramelan was received by President Saddam Hussein on Wednesday.
During the meeting, Ramelan conveyed to Saddam a letter from
Indonesian President B.J. Habibi on bilateral relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
