<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1400 GMT, October 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel released Friday morning 151 Palestinian
security prisoners under the Sharm el-Sheikh peace deal signed in
September.
</P>
<P>
Buses loaded with the prisoners left Nafha prison near Mitzeh
Ramon and Shikma prison near Ashkelon at about 4:00 am local time
(0200 GMT) and traveled to different locations between Israel and
the Palestinian territories as agreed by the two sides.(Israel-
Palestine-Prisoners)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Josef Burg, founder of Israel's National Religious
Party (NRP), died Friday at the age of 90.
</P>
<P>
Born in Dresden, Germany, Burg arrived in British-mandated
Palestine just before the outbreak of World War II in 1939. He
spent 40 years in the Knesset (parliament) after Israel's
establishment in 1948 and served as health, posts, welfare,
interior, police and religious portfolios in the government until
his retirement from politics in 1968.(Israel-Obit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Nigeria's Defense Minister Theophilus Danjuma Thursday
dismissed rumors that some people are preparing to invade Nigeria,
reported the Guardian, a leading Nigerian newspaper Friday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the minister assured that the Armed Forces of
Nigeria are capable of crushing any external aggression. (
Nigeria-Military)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- The fourth ordinary session of the fourth legislature
of the Lao National Assembly ended in Vientiane on Thursday after
endorsing the socio-economic development plan of the country, Lao
official news agency KPL reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The session, which started on September 30, also endorsed the
country's state budget for the 1999-2000 fiscal year and amended
Article 22 of the Criminal Act on adultery and seven articles of
the law on the Bank of Laos.(Laos-National Assembly)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India expressed concern Friday over the direction
in which the situation in Pakistan was moving and virtually ruled
out immediate resumption of the stalled bilateral dialogue with
Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan is effectively under martial law following a military
coup," said a spokesman of the External Affairs Ministry. "We have
concerns about the direction in which the situation is moving." (
India-Pakistan-Situation) 
</P>
