<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Meets Slovakia Parliament Delegation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
National People's Congress Standing Committee, met with a
delegation from the Slovak National Council led by its chairman
Jozef Migas, here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The China-Slovakia relationship has proceeded healthily and
stably since the two countries forged diplomatic ties, and the NPC
and the Slovak National Council have maintained normal ties, Li
said, adding his belief that the current visit will give impetus
to the further growth of the ties between both countries and both
parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Li went on to say that over the past years, bilateral
cooperation in political, economic, scientific and cultural fields
have progressed steadily, thanks to efforts from both sides.
</P>
<P>
The continual exchange of visits between leaders of both
countries has promoted mutual understanding and friendship, as
well as exchange and cooperation in various fields, added Li,
hoping that both countries further develop friendship and
cooperation in all fields including trade, on the basis of
equality and mutual-benefit.
</P>
<P>
Regarding parliamentary relations, Li said that parliament-to-
parliament exchange constitutes an important part of the state-to-
state relationship, as both the NPC and the Slovak National
Council play important roles in political life of their own
countries.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the NPC maintains active ties with the Slovak
National Council to promote understanding and expand common ground
so as to contribute to the further growth of friendship and
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
