<HEADLINE> EDS-Details China's Top Legislator Meets Slovakia Parliament Delegation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li reiterated that China adopts an independent foreign policy
of peace and respects the development paths chosen by the people
of all countries. Moreover, China advocated that the world should
"be a multi-polar world" and opposed the empty rhetoric that "
human rights is above sovereignty," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The non-violation of sovereignty is clearly written in the U.N.
Charter," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
On China's reunification, Li said that China will resume its
exercise of sovereignty over Macao on December 20 this year.
However, China still has not realized final reunification, for "
there is still a Taiwan issue," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We oppose the 'state-to-state' malice of Lee Teng-hui, for it
is against the will of the whole Chinese people, including the
Taiwan compatriots," he said. On the recent Taiwan earthquake
disaster, Li again expressed deep concern and said that China will
extend "all possible aid that can be offered."
</P>
<P>
Li expressed his appreciation for Slovakia's consistent one
China stance.
</P>
<P>
Migas said he felt honored to visit China after the election of
the new Slovak National Council in 1998 and offered his
congratulations on the 50th anniversary of the founding of new
China.
</P>
<P>
"I wish China to be a rich nation with strong people and make
greater achievements in the reform and opening-up," he told Li.
</P>
<P>
Even though Slovakia is a small country, he said, "One of the
key objects for our country is to continue to develop a good
relationship with China" for the two countries have enjoyed a long
tradition of friendship.
</P>
