<HEADLINE> Cult Leader Executed in Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The leader of the Zhu Shen
Jiao (Principal God) cult has recently been executed in Xiangtan
City of central China's Hunan province after being convicted of
rape, fraud and obstructing justice.
</P>
<P>
Liu Jiaguo, founder of the 8,000-member cult and self-
proclaimed "Principal God" of the group, was found to have raped
11 women, including two girls under age 14.
</P>
<P>
Liu's aide, Zhu Aiqing, received a 17-year prison sentence and
was fined 10,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
It was found that Liu and Zhu took swindled 220,000 yuan from
the cult through fraudulent means, and the cult's activities
caused severe social disorder in some localities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
