<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Official Circular on Civil Servants Practicing Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the State
Council recently issued a circular to local governments as well as
departments under the State Council, asking them to properly deal
with civil servants who have practiced Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Personnel and Ministry of Supervision have
jointly worked out a document on handling the issue, which should
be carried out in earnest, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
The document said that it is necessary to strictly adhere to
the central authorities' policies and enable the majority of Falun
Gong practitioners to return to the correct perspective by
educational and administrative means.
</P>
<P>
Civil servants who practiced Falun Gong will not receive any
administrative penalty if they discontinue their involvement in
Falun Gong activities, according to the document.
</P>
<P>
Even those who participated in Falun Gong's illegal gathering
will not face penalty if they clearly disengage themselves from
the organization, the document said.
</P>
<P>
However, those who took part in illegal gatherings and continue
to believe in the practices even after repeated education on the
matter will face different disciplinary actions in line with their
respective conditions, it said.
</P>
<P>
Those who have been politically motivated and have organized
illegal gatherings with a result of disturbing social order and
causing social instability should be sacked, it said.
</P>
<P>
And those who have continued to be engaged in illegal
gatherings and activities after the Ministry of Public Security
banned the organization on July 22 will be severely penalized,
according to the document.
</P>
<P>
It also said that disciplinary actions should be taken
prudently and in line with offenses, in accordance with the
Provisional Regulations on Civil Servants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
