<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua)-- The Gulbenkian Orchestra of
Portugal entertained a Chinese audience which included the
Chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress Standing
Committee Li Peng at the Great Hall of the People this evening.
</P>
<P>
The orchestra, invited by the Chinese Ministry of Culture, is
here to celebrate the coming return of Macao to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
At the intermission, Li met with Administrator of the
Gulbenkian Foundation Jose Blanco and the orchestra's chief
conductor Tang Muhai.
</P>
