the two countries following their close coordination on the issue
of Macao, he noted, and congratulated Blanco on the success of the
orchestra's performance.
</P>
<P>
Under the baton of Tang, the world-renowned conductor of
Chinese origin, the orchestra treated the audience with
compositions from Rossini, Santos, Beethoven, and a Chinese
composer Chen Xiaoyong. The selections were well-received by the
audience. 
