<HEADLINE> Pakistan Freezes Accounts of Deposed PM, Politicians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The State Bank of Pakistan
Friday froze the bank accounts of deposed Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif, senior government officials and parliamentarians and their
spouses, banking sources said.
</P>
<P>
The move came hours after the declaration of a state of
emergency by Pakistani Army Chief General Pervaiz Musharraf, who
has assumed absolute executive power and suspended the
Constitution.
</P>
