<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Kui: Less Enjoyment in All-around Competitions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The all-around competitions
here at the gymnastics world championships were not as elegant and
enjoyable as before, the Chinese team leader complained on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The error-proned all-around competitions were intense, but not
enjoyable as before. The gymnasts nowadays concentrate more on the
degree of difficulty, not the grace and beauty," said Qain Kui,
Chinese team leader who has been coaching and guiding for more
than 37 years.
</P>
<P>
World and Olympic champions Svetlana Khorkina of Russia and
Simona Amanar of Romania both faded their dreams of winning the
women's all-around crown by mistakes.
</P>
<P>
The same mishap was repeated in the men's final when defending
champion Ivan Ivankov of Belarus slumped the horizontal bar and
quit the rest five apparatus afterwards.
</P>
<P>
The failure of those veterans left the titles to the unexpected
new star Maria Olaru of Romania and Nikolay Krukov of Russia,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
"Olaru and Krukov were very good, but they have a big gap
compared with the previous world champions," said Qian, who spend
more than 40 years in gymnastics.
</P>
<P>
"The requirement of difficulty, stableness and elegance was no
longer the trend for the gymnastics nowadays, which only focuses
on complex routines. Difficulty always cause failure for gymnasts
and departure from the audience," Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Asked about possible development of gymnastics, Qian preferred
artistry to difficulty.
</P>
<P>
"The ideal gymnastics should bring enjoyment to the audience,
as well as gymnasts themselves, like Khorkina," said Qian.
</P>
<P>
Khokina, who displayed her trademark of invincible elegance and
won the uneven bars title in 9.837 at the world gymnastics
championships here on Friday, proved that the artistry still could
lead the way of gymnastics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
