<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Company to Handle State Assets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China's largest trade and
financial city established a company today to help with the
restructuring of state-owned enterprises (SOEs).
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai State Assets Management Co., Ltd., which opened
today, is considered a strategic move in reshuffling of the city's
SOEs.
</P>
<P>
Chen Liangyu, deputy mayor of Shanghai, said that the company
will help optimize the industrial structure of Shanghai and reform
the city's SOEs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
