<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gunmen Kill 2 People in Mogadishu's Cinema </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- At least two people were
killed and more than five others wounded when unidentified gunmen
attacked a cinema hall in south Mogadishu on Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said Friday that three armed men and a barehanded
one attacked the cinema, Theatre Towfiq, at a time when dozens of
spectators were watching a movie early in the evening.
</P>
<P>
The owner, Ali Dhuh, and one of the spectators died instantly
while the technician operating the video machine was seriously
wounded.
</P>
<P>
The wounded spectators also included a woman and a child, who
were immediately rushed to a nearby treatment center.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the attack is not known. And no one has claimed
 responsibility for the incident.
</P>
<P>
Some sources said the attack had some thing to do with a
religious group which disliked the movies displayed to the public
in that particular cinema.
</P>
<P>
Early in the year, unknown gunmen and a group of people
attacked a brothel near Bar Ubah junction, not far from Theatre
Towfiq on the same Soddonkah street.
</P>
<P>
Mob justice increases in the Somali capital, especially in the
public areas including the cinema halls, brothels and market
places where gunmen with different motives attack the civilians.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
