<DOCNO> XIE19991015.0582 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Dominates Apparatus Finals at Gymnastics Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Russian Alexei Nemov showed he was still the man to beat as he
claimed the floor title with 9.787 points here on Friday for the
first gold of Russia.
</P>
<P>
It was also the first medal of the Atlanta Olympic champion who
has been struggling with the injury and performed sluggishly in
the individual all-round competition on Thursday where he only
finished sixth.
</P>
<P>
Gervasio Deferr of Spain was the runner-up on 9.750 points with
Chinese Xing Aowei placing third on 9.737 points.
</P>
<P>
Nemov continued his winning momentum to take the pommel horse
title on 9.775 points, beating Marius Urzica of Romania and
Nikolay Krukov of Russia.
</P>
<P>
Marius earned 9.762 points and Nikolay, who upset a strong
field to win the individual all-round title on Thursday, finished
9.750.
</P>
<P>
"It was an expected victory of gold-double," said the excited
Nemov. "I was not sure to participate in this championships for my
back injury until September."
</P>
<P>
Russia's third title went to the women's vault where Elena
Zamolodchikova, who finished third at the women's individual all-
round competition on Thursday, ended up with 9.718 points.
</P>
<P>
Simona Amanar of Romania came in second on 9.631 and the
Romanian Maria Olaru who was the newly crowned champion in the all-
round, placed third on 9.593.
</P>
<P>
Svetlana Khorkina of Russia added the last gold for Russia as
she beat the challenges from Chinese rivals Huang Mandan and lin
Jie to win the uneven bars with 9.837 points.
</P>
<P>
Huang came in second on 9.825 points and Lin placed third on 9.
812.
</P>
<P>
"I had a strong feeling that I will win the game. And what I
expected came true now, I am very, very happy," said the 21-year-
old Khorkina.
</P>
<P>
"I prepared well before this championships. I didn't know why I
failed to perform my best for last days of competition. But now, I
can tell you that I will show you my favorite floor exercise
tomorrow," said the world and Olympic champion.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Dong Zhen won the last gold of the day as he earned 9.
775 points to take the title of the rings.
</P>
<P>
Szilveszter Csollany of Hungary was the runner-up on 9.737 and
Dimosthenis Tambakos of Germany third at 9.712. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
